even like them very much.

00:03:03.830 --> 00:03:05.290 align:middle line:90%
And then you have to choose.

00:03:05.290 --> 00:03:06.800 align:middle line:90%
Love is a behavior.

00:03:06.800 --> 00:03:07.675 align:middle line:90%
Love is a commitment.

00:03:07.675 --> 00:03:08.870 align:middle line:90%
Love is a choice.

00:03:08.870 --> 00:03:10.640 align:middle line:90%
Love is a decision.

00:03:10.640 --> 00:03:11.870 align:middle line:90%
And it's work.

00:03:11.870 --> 00:03:12.940 align:middle line:90%
It really is work.

00:03:12.940 --> 00:03:15.200 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, oh,
I'm with my soulmate.

00:03:15.200 --> 00:03:16.830 align:middle line:84%
It must mean it's
going to be easy.

00:03:16.830 --> 00:03:17.890 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yeah, a
happily ever after.

00:03:17.890 --> 00:03:18.970 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yeah, right?

00:03:18.970 --> 00:03:21.740 align:middle line:84%
Well, thank God for
happily even after.

00:03:21.740 --> 00:03:23.440 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah, that's true.

00:03:23.440 --> 00:03:24.460 align:middle line:90%
That's a good point.

00:03:24.460 --> 00:03:25.910 align:middle line:90%
And, you know, it's interesting.

00:03:25.910 --> 00:03:28.020 align:middle line:84%
I've looked around,
and throughout my life,

00:03:28.020 --> 00:03:32.680 align:middle line:84%
at people who seem to
naturally be adept at making

00:03:32.680 --> 00:03:33.940 align:middle line:90%
their relationship work.

00:03:33.940 --> 00:03:38.410 align:middle line:84%
And I actually
only seen a couple.

00:03:38.410 --> 00:03:41.690 align:middle line:84%
Honestly, if I'm being-- yeah,
if I am being honest, and I am,

00:03:41.690 --> 00:03:43.210 align:middle line:90%
I've only seen a couple people.

00:03:43.210 --> 00:03:45.000 align:middle line:84%
And one of them
is a woman who is

00:03:45.000 --> 00:03:48.900 align:middle line:84%
a former sister in law
of mine whose birthday is

00:03:48.900 --> 00:03:51.550 align:middle line:90%
February 14, Valentine's Day.

00:03:51.550 --> 00:03:57.060 align:middle line:84%
And this woman just has a
type of grace and enthusiasm

00:03:57.060 --> 00:03:58.940 align:middle line:84%
for life, where
she married someone

00:03:58.940 --> 00:04:02.080 align:middle line:84%
who was her polar opposite,
the ballerina cowboy syndrome

00:04:02.080 --> 00:04:06.110 align:middle line:90%
thing, and had six children.

00:04:06.110 --> 00:04:10.920 align:middle line:84%
And every day, still remains
a creative endeavor that she--

00:04:10.920 --> 00:04:13.910 align:middle line:84%
that she is solely responsible
for, in terms of being the glue

00:04:13.910 --> 00:04:15.810 align:middle line:84%
that family and
that love affair.

00:04:15.810 --> 00:04:17.149 align:middle line:90%
And it's still a love affair.

00:04:17.149 --> 00:04:17.733 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yeah.

00:04:17.733 --> 00:04:20.273 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: But that's the only
person I've seen that's really

00:04:20.273 --> 00:04:21.740 align:middle line:90%
just known how to do it somehow.

00:04:21.740 --> 00:04:22.860 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: It's rare.

00:04:22.860 --> 00:04:26.850 align:middle line:84%
I have a lot of friends that
are married to their soulmate

00:04:26.850 --> 00:04:29.622 align:middle line:84%
and they still have to
work at the relationship.

00:04:29.622 --> 00:04:31.330 align:middle line:84%
Because there's so
much that we come in--

00:04:31.330 --> 00:04:34.140 align:middle line:84%
and I really believe
soulmates come in together

00:04:34.140 --> 00:04:37.060 align:middle line:84%
with sacred contracts
to be together.

00:04:37.060 --> 00:04:39.600 align:middle line:84%
There's past life stuff,
and there's karma,

00:04:39.600 --> 00:04:42.270 align:middle line:84%
and there's choices that
we make in between lives.

00:04:42.270 --> 00:04:45.790 align:middle line:84%
OK, yeah, let's be soulmates
in this next lifetime and let's

00:04:45.790 --> 00:04:48.870 align:middle line:84%
set up these synchronicities
so we recognize each other.

00:04:48.870 --> 00:04:51.970 align:middle line:84%
And let's work out the fact
that in the three past lives

00:04:51.970 --> 00:04:54.340 align:middle line:84%
you betrayed me and we're
going to have betrayal issues

00:04:54.340 --> 00:04:56.810 align:middle line:84%
and we're going to have
so many kids together.

00:04:56.810 --> 00:04:57.970 align:middle line:90%
But we forget all that.

00:04:57.970 --> 00:04:59.220 align:middle line:90%
We meet them.

00:04:59.220 --> 00:05:00.690 align:middle line:90%
We fall in love.

00:05:00.690 --> 00:05:02.710 align:middle line:90%
We're in this euphoric state.

00:05:02.710 --> 00:05:05.710 align:middle line:84%
We're in what I call the
socially acceptable form

00:05:05.710 --> 00:05:08.260 align:middle line:84%
of insanity,
because the dopamine

00:05:08.260 --> 00:05:11.980 align:middle line:84%
and the adrenalin and the
oxytocin's all kicking off.

00:05:11.980 --> 00:05:15.230 align:middle line:84%
And it's great for
6 to 18 months,

00:05:15.230 --> 00:05:17.420 align:middle line:84%
until all the
chemistry goes away.

00:05:17.420 --> 00:05:19.870 align:middle line:84%
And, suddenly, this
person with which

00:05:19.870 --> 00:05:24.050 align:middle line:84%
you had such frequency
and synchronicity with

00:05:24.050 --> 00:05:25.380 align:middle line:90%
is just a real human being.

00:05:25.380 --> 00:05:28.490 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yeah, see, I've
always viewed that as the hook,

00:05:28.490 --> 00:05:29.729 align:middle line:90%
as the soul's hook.

00:05:29.729 --> 00:05:30.270 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yes.

00:05:30.270 --> 00:05:34.210 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: The means of drawing
people together for either

00:05:34.210 --> 00:05:36.540 align:middle line:84%
something very lovely,
creative, and pleasurable,

00:05:36.540 --> 00:05:39.260 align:middle line:84%
or for learning, which may
feel the opposite of that.

00:05:39.260 --> 00:05:44.690 align:middle line:84%
Both are equally as valuable,
but that chemical cascade

00:05:44.690 --> 00:05:47.747 align:middle line:84%
I do believe is a projection
from the soul to say tt-tt-tt,

00:05:47.747 --> 00:05:48.330 align:middle line:90%
don't go away.

00:05:48.330 --> 00:05:48.810 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: It's nature's trick.

00:05:48.810 --> 00:05:49.685 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Stay here.

00:05:49.685 --> 00:05:52.950 align:middle line:84%
It's a trick to keep
you together long enough

00:05:52.950 --> 00:05:56.340 align:middle line:84%
to establish some other bond so
that you can dig down and start

00:05:56.340 --> 00:05:57.620 align:middle line:90%
doing your thing together.

00:05:57.620 --> 00:05:58.880 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Exactly, yes.

00:05:58.880 --> 00:05:59.710 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: So it can be tricky.

00:05:59.710 --> 00:06:02.270 align:middle line:84%
Because, a lot of times, like
when you say the chemicals wear

00:06:02.270 --> 00:06:04.650 align:middle line:90%
off, it's what was I thinking.

00:06:04.650 --> 00:06:05.630 align:middle line:90%
Well, you weren't.

00:06:05.630 --> 00:06:06.655 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't your choice.

00:06:06.655 --> 00:06:08.270 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: It had nothing to
do with rational thought.

00:06:08.270 --> 00:06:09.311 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: No, it didn't.

00:06:09.311 --> 00:06:12.470 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: But it's an important
piece of it because soulmates

00:06:12.470 --> 00:06:17.110 align:middle line:84%
come together to heal each
other on the deepest level.

00:06:17.110 --> 00:06:20.090 align:middle line:84%
And as anybody interested
in personal growth knows,

00:06:20.090 --> 00:06:21.820 align:middle line:90%
the healing part sucks.

00:06:21.820 --> 00:06:22.950 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't feel good.

00:06:22.950 --> 00:06:24.040 align:middle line:90%
It's not fun.

00:06:24.040 --> 00:06:25.900 align:middle line:90%
It's often painful.

00:06:25.900 --> 00:06:29.820 align:middle line:84%
Harville Hendrix, who Oprah
calls the marriage whisperer,

00:06:29.820 --> 00:06:32.240 align:middle line:84%
he's one of the world's
leading marriage researchers.

00:06:32.240 --> 00:06:34.190 align:middle line:84%
And we were talking
about this one day

00:06:34.190 --> 00:06:36.400 align:middle line:84%
and I said to him,
Harville, how do

00:06:36.400 --> 00:06:38.440 align:middle line:84%
you know if you're in
the right relationship?

00:06:38.440 --> 00:06:39.530 align:middle line:90%
And he started laughing.

00:06:39.530 --> 00:06:41.670 align:middle line:84%
And when he stopped
laughing, he said

00:06:41.670 --> 00:06:43.690 align:middle line:84%
you know you're in
the right relationship

00:06:43.690 --> 00:06:48.130 align:middle line:84%
when it starts off as a dream
come true and eventually

00:06:48.130 --> 00:06:50.940 align:middle line:84%
devolves into your
worst nightmare.

00:06:50.940 --> 00:06:51.780 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Exactly.

00:06:51.780 --> 00:06:55.300 align:middle line:84%
I think that's my
observation and my experience

00:06:55.300 --> 00:07:00.360 align:middle line:84%
as well, in that if you didn't
have that chemical cascade,

00:07:00.360 --> 00:07:03.130 align:middle line:84%
saying, oh, my god,
this is just amazing,

00:07:03.130 --> 00:07:06.285 align:middle line:84%
there is no incentive to
stick in with the situation.

00:07:06.285 --> 00:07:06.910 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Right.

00:07:06.910 --> 00:07:08.600 align:middle line:90%
And you're in that state.

00:07:08.600 --> 00:07:09.705 align:middle line:90%
Water tastes wetter.

00:07:09.705 --> 00:07:10.330 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:07:10.330 --> 00:07:11.664 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Air smells sweeter.

00:07:11.664 --> 00:07:12.330 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:07:12.330 --> 00:07:14.200 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Everything
feels so good.

00:07:14.200 --> 00:07:15.270 align:middle line:90%
And then it goes away.

00:07:15.270 --> 00:07:17.000 align:middle line:84%
And there's this
big disappointment.

00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:19.290 align:middle line:84%
Oh, does this mean I
don't love him anymore

00:07:19.290 --> 00:07:21.190 align:middle line:90%
or she doesn't love me anymore?

00:07:21.190 --> 00:07:25.910 align:middle line:84%
But the truth is all of those
chemicals are still there.

00:07:25.910 --> 00:07:28.060 align:middle line:84%
They're now covered
up with reality.

00:07:28.060 --> 00:07:30.970 align:middle line:84%
And the reason I wrote "Turn
Your Mate Into Your Soulmate"

00:07:30.970 --> 00:07:35.770 align:middle line:84%
was to show you how to
reignite those chemicals to get

00:07:35.770 --> 00:07:39.050 align:middle line:84%
those feelings back
and to reenvision

00:07:39.050 --> 00:07:40.820 align:middle line:90%
the relationship that you have.

00:07:40.820 --> 00:07:42.560 align:middle line:84%
Because as you
said in the intro,

00:07:42.560 --> 00:07:46.690 align:middle line:84%
everybody knows that 50% of
first marriages end in divorce.

00:07:46.690 --> 00:07:51.475 align:middle line:84%
What most people don't know is
that 64% of second marriages--

00:07:51.475 --> 00:07:52.350 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: And it's--

00:07:52.350 --> 00:07:56.074 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: 73% of third
marriages end in divorce.

00:07:56.074 --> 00:07:56.740 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:07:56.740 --> 00:08:01.020 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: So if you're looking
like the problem's over there,

00:08:01.020 --> 00:08:01.890 align:middle line:90%
that's not true.

00:08:01.890 --> 00:08:04.685 align:middle line:84%
Because the person who's in
all three marriages is you.

00:08:04.685 --> 00:08:06.310 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And as
we'll discover later,

00:08:06.310 --> 00:08:08.030 align:middle line:90%
maybe it's not even a problem.

00:08:08.030 --> 00:08:11.740 align:middle line:84%
So let's start out with
your definition of soulmate.

00:08:11.740 --> 00:08:14.580 align:middle line:84%
Because that means different
things to do different people.

00:08:14.580 --> 00:08:15.750 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yeah, it's true.

00:08:15.750 --> 00:08:17.690 align:middle line:84%
So my definition
of a soulmate is

00:08:17.690 --> 00:08:21.380 align:middle line:84%
that it's first and foremost
somebody you can completely

00:08:21.380 --> 00:08:23.930 align:middle line:84%
be yourself with,
somebody with whom

00:08:23.930 --> 00:08:26.480 align:middle line:84%
you share unconditional
love, and when

00:08:26.480 --> 00:08:28.520 align:middle line:84%
you look into their
eyes, you have

00:08:28.520 --> 00:08:31.310 align:middle line:90%
the experience of being home.

00:08:31.310 --> 00:08:33.679 align:middle line:84%
And if you accept
that definition,

00:08:33.679 --> 00:08:35.620 align:middle line:84%
then I want to expand
it even further.

00:08:35.620 --> 00:08:37.440 align:middle line:84%
Because we're
going to be talking

00:08:37.440 --> 00:08:41.450 align:middle line:84%
about romantic soulmates today,
but your kids, your parents,

00:08:41.450 --> 00:08:44.820 align:middle line:84%
your siblings, your co-workers,
your best friend, your cat,

00:08:44.820 --> 00:08:49.860 align:middle line:84%
your dog all are also soulmates
if they fit that definition.

00:08:49.860 --> 00:08:52.440 align:middle line:84%
And to take it even a
step further than that,

00:08:52.440 --> 00:08:55.770 align:middle line:84%
I would also say a
soulmate is somebody

00:08:55.770 --> 00:08:59.850 align:middle line:84%
that you feel emotionally
and physically safe with.

00:08:59.850 --> 00:09:02.250 align:middle line:84%
So if you're in a
relationship where there's

00:09:02.250 --> 00:09:07.760 align:middle line:84%
abuse, extreme addiction,
or really bad behavior,

00:09:07.760 --> 00:09:08.660 align:middle line:90%
I can't help you.

00:09:08.660 --> 00:09:10.760 align:middle line:84%
This is why God
invented therapists.

00:09:10.760 --> 00:09:12.310 align:middle line:90%
You need professionals.

00:09:12.310 --> 00:09:15.470 align:middle line:84%
But for anybody else
who's bored, disappointed,

