with us for a little while
longer and take some baby

00:09:23.280 --> 00:09:27.880 align:middle line:84%
steps, it is-- it's definitely
possible to rediscover

00:09:27.880 --> 00:09:30.600 align:middle line:84%
the love, and the
passion, and the fun.

00:09:30.600 --> 00:09:33.030 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: OK, so this is
bringing a couple of questions

00:09:33.030 --> 00:09:33.530 align:middle line:90%
up.

00:09:33.530 --> 00:09:38.290 align:middle line:84%
One, we tend to-- we tend
to circulate within a given

00:09:38.290 --> 00:09:40.900 align:middle line:90%
incarnation with a soul tribe.

00:09:40.900 --> 00:09:43.640 align:middle line:84%
So any time we run into the
member of that soul tribe,

00:09:43.640 --> 00:09:45.885 align:middle line:84%
it has that soulmate
kind of feeling.

00:09:45.885 --> 00:09:46.580 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yes.

00:09:46.580 --> 00:09:49.240 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Whether it's a
family member, friend, lover,

00:09:49.240 --> 00:09:49.960 align:middle line:90%
or whatnot.

00:09:49.960 --> 00:09:51.090 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: The recognition.

00:09:51.090 --> 00:09:52.214 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: The recognition.

00:09:52.214 --> 00:09:54.820 align:middle line:84%
So that-- by virtue
of that alone,

00:09:54.820 --> 00:09:59.189 align:middle line:84%
we're falling into karmic
patterns, incarnation patterns.

00:09:59.189 --> 00:09:59.730 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yes.

00:09:59.730 --> 00:10:01.480 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So that's
where that recogniz--

00:10:01.480 --> 00:10:03.440 align:middle line:84%
so when people have that
instant recognition,

00:10:03.440 --> 00:10:06.870 align:middle line:84%
you can pretty much guess you
have been traveling together

00:10:06.870 --> 00:10:07.480 align:middle line:90%
before.

00:10:07.480 --> 00:10:09.940 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: But the mistake a lot
of people make is they feel

00:10:09.940 --> 00:10:12.880 align:middle line:84%
that connection,
that recognition.

00:10:12.880 --> 00:10:15.300 align:middle line:84%
And if it's a-- if
there's chemistry

00:10:15.300 --> 00:10:17.330 align:middle line:84%
and there's some
sexuality there,

00:10:17.330 --> 00:10:21.679 align:middle line:84%
they leap to the conclusion, oh,
this must be my life partner.

00:10:21.679 --> 00:10:22.470 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Exactly.

00:10:22.470 --> 00:10:24.115 align:middle line:84%
And that is not
necessarily true.

00:10:24.115 --> 00:10:24.740 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Right.

00:10:24.740 --> 00:10:29.420 align:middle line:84%
Because in order to have a
sustainable happy marriage,

00:10:29.420 --> 00:10:31.270 align:middle line:84%
you need more than
the recognition,

00:10:31.270 --> 00:10:32.830 align:middle line:90%
more than the chemistry.

00:10:32.830 --> 00:10:39.180 align:middle line:84%
You need communication,
connection, compatibility,

00:10:39.180 --> 00:10:43.410 align:middle line:84%
and, most importantly, a
shared vision for the future.

00:10:43.410 --> 00:10:46.540 align:middle line:84%
If you're somebody like me
who loves to travel the world

00:10:46.540 --> 00:10:49.930 align:middle line:84%
and wants exotic travel,
and I fall in love with you

00:10:49.930 --> 00:10:52.510 align:middle line:84%
and you're an
agoraphobic, we are not

00:10:52.510 --> 00:10:54.612 align:middle line:90%
going to be happy together.

00:10:54.612 --> 00:10:55.320 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:10:55.320 --> 00:10:59.060 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: So this is why it's so
important that you could lock

00:10:59.060 --> 00:11:02.610 align:middle line:84%
eyes across a crowded
room, you are the one.

00:11:02.610 --> 00:11:04.430 align:middle line:90%
But don't get married tomorrow.

00:11:04.430 --> 00:11:08.160 align:middle line:84%
Spend a good solid year dating
and getting to know them.

00:11:08.160 --> 00:11:10.510 align:middle line:84%
And are they your
lifelong partner?

00:11:10.510 --> 00:11:11.810 align:middle line:90%
Do they have that potential?

00:11:11.810 --> 00:11:14.351 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And whatever it is
between you may well be cleared

00:11:14.351 --> 00:11:15.295 align:middle line:90%
within that year.

00:11:15.295 --> 00:11:15.560 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yes.

00:11:15.560 --> 00:11:17.660 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Acknowledged and
cleared within that year.

00:11:17.660 --> 00:11:19.340 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to go
through a marriage

00:11:19.340 --> 00:11:20.250 align:middle line:84%
to figure that one
out necessarily.

00:11:20.250 --> 00:11:20.958 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Exactly.

00:11:20.958 --> 00:11:22.670 align:middle line:84%
Because, sometimes,
it's just you

00:11:22.670 --> 00:11:26.694 align:middle line:84%
come together for a reason,
or a season, or a lifetime.

00:11:26.694 --> 00:11:29.110 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Let's talk about
another situation that I think

00:11:29.110 --> 00:11:32.210 align:middle line:84%
probably everybody watching,
most people, at least,

00:11:32.210 --> 00:11:35.830 align:middle line:84%
have had happen, where you're
somewhere and you meet a total

00:11:35.830 --> 00:11:38.610 align:middle line:90%
stranger for about 15 minutes.

00:11:38.610 --> 00:11:41.850 align:middle line:84%
And it's like you know
everything about that person.

00:11:41.850 --> 00:11:45.830 align:middle line:84%
There's absolute unconditional
love there, everything,

00:11:45.830 --> 00:11:49.670 align:middle line:84%
but it's really nothing more
than just a passing moment.

00:11:49.670 --> 00:11:50.330 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: It is.

00:11:50.330 --> 00:11:51.540 align:middle line:90%
And that's what it is.

00:11:51.540 --> 00:11:53.760 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes we
have to accept it.

00:11:53.760 --> 00:11:57.710 align:middle line:84%
And yet people will spend
years pining for it.

00:11:57.710 --> 00:12:00.864 align:middle line:84%
Oh, I met him, but he got on
the train and he got away.

00:12:00.864 --> 00:12:02.780 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I think there's
a James Blunt song.

00:12:02.780 --> 00:12:04.405 align:middle line:84%
I think it was James
Blunt, about that.

00:12:04.405 --> 00:12:05.441 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yeah.

00:12:05.441 --> 00:12:08.610 align:middle line:84%
And the truth is that's
because we live with the myth

00:12:08.610 --> 00:12:11.759 align:middle line:84%
that we each only get one
big love in a lifetime.

00:12:11.759 --> 00:12:13.550 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And we're
going to go into that.

00:12:13.550 --> 00:12:16.200 align:middle line:84%
Now, let's go back
to you and Brian.

00:12:16.200 --> 00:12:17.650 align:middle line:90%
So you're 44 years old.

00:12:17.650 --> 00:12:20.570 align:middle line:84%
You have no template for what
a relationship even looks like.

00:12:20.570 --> 00:12:20.800 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Right.

00:12:20.800 --> 00:12:22.270 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Chemicals
are cascading.

00:12:22.270 --> 00:12:24.730 align:middle line:84%
You're having a lot of
fun, happily ever after,

00:12:24.730 --> 00:12:26.580 align:middle line:90%
and then the reality sets in.

00:12:26.580 --> 00:12:27.960 align:middle line:90%
How did this all work for you?

00:12:27.960 --> 00:12:31.600 align:middle line:84%
How did it start-- how did the
disappointment start showing up

00:12:31.600 --> 00:12:33.440 align:middle line:90%
for you and Brian?

00:12:33.440 --> 00:12:36.900 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Well, I started to
notice that very often he was

00:12:36.900 --> 00:12:40.600 align:middle line:84%
saying to me you are
not listening to me.

00:12:40.600 --> 00:12:44.500 align:middle line:84%
And my immediate reaction
was to get defensive and then

00:12:44.500 --> 00:12:47.435 align:middle line:84%
parrot back to him whatever
it was he just said.

00:12:47.435 --> 00:12:48.810 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: To show
you're smart--

00:12:48.810 --> 00:12:49.260 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: To prove--

00:12:49.260 --> 00:12:49.910 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And now
you've proven it.

00:12:49.910 --> 00:12:50.840 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Right.

00:12:50.840 --> 00:12:53.280 align:middle line:84%
But the truth was, and I
knew what the truth was,

00:12:53.280 --> 00:12:55.620 align:middle line:90%
is I have a tendency to drift.

00:12:55.620 --> 00:12:57.220 align:middle line:90%
I am an oldest child.

00:12:57.220 --> 00:12:59.600 align:middle line:90%
I am a terrible listener.

00:12:59.600 --> 00:13:03.330 align:middle line:84%
My life is all about me
and what's in it for me.

00:13:03.330 --> 00:13:05.830 align:middle line:84%
Brian, on the other hand,
is the youngest child,

00:13:05.830 --> 00:13:10.580 align:middle line:84%
whose deepest core need is to be
seen and heard and listened to.

00:13:10.580 --> 00:13:14.310 align:middle line:84%
And he's used to getting that
from everybody around him.

00:13:14.310 --> 00:13:16.080 align:middle line:90%
So we were perfect together.

00:13:16.080 --> 00:13:18.890 align:middle line:84%
Both of our childhood
issues were knocking up

00:13:18.890 --> 00:13:20.500 align:middle line:90%
against each other.

00:13:20.500 --> 00:13:23.220 align:middle line:84%
But I didn't understand
it at the time.

00:13:23.220 --> 00:13:25.070 align:middle line:84%
I was just like what's
the matter with him.

00:13:25.070 --> 00:13:28.340 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, he just said A, B, and
C. So that was the first thing.

00:13:28.340 --> 00:13:30.550 align:middle line:84%
And it was really
uncomfortable because I

00:13:30.550 --> 00:13:34.120 align:middle line:84%
was hearing a tone in his
voice and seeing body language

00:13:34.120 --> 00:13:37.420 align:middle line:84%
that I hadn't seen
18 months previously.

00:13:37.420 --> 00:13:39.100 align:middle line:90%
And I was disappointing him.

00:13:39.100 --> 00:13:42.740 align:middle line:84%
And the last thing I wanted
to do was disappoint him.

00:13:42.740 --> 00:13:46.450 align:middle line:84%
And then another thing happened
that in retrospect is very

00:13:46.450 --> 00:13:48.790 align:middle line:84%
funny now, but at
the time, wasn't.

00:13:48.790 --> 00:13:51.513 align:middle line:84%
One day, I caught myself
like this in front of him.

00:13:51.513 --> 00:13:52.480 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Oops.

00:13:52.480 --> 00:13:55.200 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: And I don't remember
what I was ragging on him

00:13:55.200 --> 00:14:00.660 align:middle line:84%
about, but I saw myself like
this and I immediately stopped.

00:14:00.660 --> 00:14:02.460 align:middle line:90%
And I was embarrassed.

00:14:02.460 --> 00:14:06.780 align:middle line:84%
And I said to him the
next time this happens,

00:14:06.780 --> 00:14:08.590 align:middle line:84%
and, unfortunately,
there's going

00:14:08.590 --> 00:14:11.570 align:middle line:84%
to be a next time,
could you just kindly,

00:14:11.570 --> 00:14:15.990 align:middle line:84%
sweetly, gently say to me, "when
did Sheila enter the room?"

00:14:15.990 --> 00:14:18.880 align:middle line:84%
Now, Sheila's my mother's
name, and I adore my mother.

00:14:18.880 --> 00:14:20.310 align:middle line:90%
She's very cool.

00:14:20.310 --> 00:14:24.500 align:middle line:84%
But she can be very bossy
and overbearing, as can I.

00:14:24.500 --> 00:14:26.060 align:middle line:90%
And he was so cool about it.

00:14:26.060 --> 00:14:26.840 align:middle line:90%
He totally got it.

00:14:26.840 --> 00:14:27.970 align:middle line:90%
He said yes.

00:14:27.970 --> 00:14:29.840 align:middle line:84%
And the next time
I'm too patronizing,

00:14:29.840 --> 00:14:31.580 align:middle line:90%
you can call me Wayne.

00:14:31.580 --> 00:14:33.660 align:middle line:90%
That was his dad's name, right?

00:14:33.660 --> 00:14:37.250 align:middle line:84%
So very quickly we
eliminated the possibility

00:14:37.250 --> 00:14:40.090 align:middle line:84%
of World War III because
we had these code names.

00:14:40.090 --> 00:14:41.940 align:middle line:84%
And even to this day,
occasionally, he'll

00:14:41.940 --> 00:14:44.155 align:middle line:84%
say, oh, I can see
Sheila just walked in.

00:14:44.155 --> 00:14:44.780 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:14:44.780 --> 00:14:46.190 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: So that helps.

00:14:46.190 --> 00:14:48.480 align:middle line:84%
But I had been used
to running a business.

00:14:48.480 --> 00:14:50.800 align:middle line:90%
I was used to being the boss.

00:14:50.800 --> 00:14:54.201 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't know how unsexy
being the boss in a marriage

00:14:54.201 --> 00:14:54.700 align:middle line:90%
was.

00:14:54.700 --> 00:14:55.970 align:middle line:90%
I had no clue.

00:14:55.970 --> 00:14:58.140 align:middle line:84%
I was living in my
masculine energy.

00:14:58.140 --> 00:15:00.330 align:middle line:84%
I loved being in my
masculine energy.

00:15:00.330 --> 00:15:03.470 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't know that when
you marry an alpha male,

00:15:03.470 --> 00:15:06.032 align:middle line:84%
you can't have two men
in the relationship

00:15:06.032 --> 00:15:07.740 align:middle line:84%
if you're ever going
to really get along.

00:15:07.740 --> 00:15:10.817 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: This is a big
problem in the west right now.

00:15:10.817 --> 00:15:11.400 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Huge.

00:15:11.400 --> 00:15:13.858 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Because women have
been on their own a long time

00:15:13.858 --> 00:15:14.615 align:middle line:90%
paying the bills.

00:15:14.615 --> 00:15:15.240 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Right.

00:15:15.240 --> 00:15:17.700 align:middle line:90%
And I didn't know.

00:15:17.700 --> 00:15:19.750 align:middle line:90%
I had studied Dr. Pat Allen.

00:15:19.750 --> 00:15:21.700 align:middle line:84%
I knew about masculine
and feminine energy,

00:15:21.700 --> 00:15:23.860 align:middle line:84%
but somehow I didn't
think it applied to me.

00:15:23.860 --> 00:15:26.210 align:middle line:84%
And I realized that
what I needed to do

00:15:26.210 --> 00:15:27.820 align:middle line:84%
was that it was fine
when I'm running

00:15:27.820 --> 00:15:29.660 align:middle line:90%
my business all day long.

00:15:29.660 --> 00:15:31.100 align:middle line:90%
I can be the boss.

00:15:31.100 --> 00:15:35.180 align:middle line:84%
But when I get home, I needed
to create a system to drop back

00:15:35.180 --> 00:15:37.100 align:middle line:90%
into my feminine energy.

00:15:37.100 --> 00:15:40.100 align:middle line:84%
So I would come home and
I would take a bubble bath

00:15:40.100 --> 00:15:43.680 align:middle line:84%
or I would do some belly dancing
or I'd listen some music.

00:15:43.680 --> 00:15:46.640 align:middle line:84%
And then I would put--
put on fresh makeup.

00:15:46.640 --> 00:15:50.620 align:middle line:84%
And I would actually downshift
back into my feminine energy.

00:15:50.620 --> 00:15:52.340 align:middle line:84%
That's what I needed
to do now for Brian.

00:15:52.340 --> 00:15:54.610 align:middle line:90%
We had a business together.

00:15:54.610 --> 00:15:56.420 align:middle line:90%
So we'd go out to dinner.

00:15:56.420 --> 00:15:59.960 align:middle line:84%
And at 8 o'clock at night, he'd
start talking contracts to me.

00:15:59.960 --> 00:16:02.350 align:middle line:84%
And I like to say to
him, no, no, no, we

00:16:02.350 --> 00:16:03.810 align:middle line:90%
can't talk business now.

00:16:03.810 --> 00:16:08.340 align:middle line:84%
I just spent an hour getting
out of my male energy head.

00:16:08.340 --> 00:16:11.450 align:middle line:84%
And as interesting
as you are, we can't.

00:16:11.450 --> 00:16:14.900 align:middle line:84%
And so we had to negotiate
that and it took about a year

00:16:14.900 --> 00:16:17.580 align:middle line:84%
until we finally
got into a pattern

00:16:17.580 --> 00:16:22.556 align:middle line:84%
where we could understand that
what we needed was polarity.

00:16:22.556 --> 00:16:23.930 align:middle line:84%
And we could shift
back and forth

00:16:23.930 --> 00:16:26.310 align:middle line:84%
because he's very comfortable
in his feminine energy.

00:16:26.310 --> 00:16:28.510 align:middle line:90%
But that took time.

00:16:28.510 --> 00:16:32.270 align:middle line:84%
So it was learning
the stuff that I

00:16:32.270 --> 00:16:35.850 align:middle line:84%
didn't know that I didn't
know was a process.

00:16:35.850 --> 00:16:38.280 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: But, clearly, the
incentive was there for you

00:16:38.280 --> 00:16:40.600 align:middle line:90%
to have this one work.

00:16:40.600 --> 00:16:43.620 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Well, not only that,
I quickly realized that if I

00:16:43.620 --> 00:16:48.530 align:middle line:84%
didn't learn to listen to him,
he would need to find somebody

00:16:48.530 --> 00:16:49.340 align:middle line:90%
who would.

00:16:49.340 --> 00:16:51.316 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:16:51.316 --> 00:16:52.690 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: And to
this day, I mean,

00:16:52.690 --> 00:16:55.760 align:middle line:84%
we're together now
almost 19 years,

00:16:55.760 --> 00:16:59.480 align:middle line:84%
there are still moments when
I have to remind myself, oh,

00:16:59.480 --> 00:17:02.880 align:middle line:84%
you need to pay attention,
which means turning towards him,

00:17:02.880 --> 00:17:05.170 align:middle line:84%
putting my phone
away, listening,

00:17:05.170 --> 00:17:07.030 align:middle line:84%
even if it's not all
that interesting.

00:17:07.030 --> 00:17:09.217 align:middle line:84%
Now, most of the time,
he's pretty fascinating.

00:17:09.217 --> 00:17:11.800 align:middle line:84%
But there are moments where the
thoughts going through my head

00:17:11.800 --> 00:17:16.040 align:middle line:84%
is like, oh, I really
need to check my email.

00:17:16.040 --> 00:17:18.430 align:middle line:90%
But what is my commitment?

00:17:18.430 --> 00:17:20.720 align:middle line:90%
My commitment is to be loving.

00:17:20.720 --> 00:17:23.819 align:middle line:84%
And what's the most loving
thing I can do in this moment?

00:17:23.819 --> 00:17:25.530 align:middle line:90%
Give him my full attention.

00:17:25.530 --> 00:17:27.940 align:middle line:84%
Because what it's more
important than him?

00:17:27.940 --> 00:17:33.270 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: OK, so now, from that
platform, I'm a good listener.

00:17:33.270 --> 00:17:35.280 align:middle line:90%
I can be a good listener.

00:17:35.280 --> 00:17:37.270 align:middle line:90%
I have to for a living, right?

00:17:37.270 --> 00:17:40.020 align:middle line:84%
But in personal relationship,
it's a little bit different

00:17:40.020 --> 00:17:42.800 align:middle line:84%
because, yes, I
can hear the words,

00:17:42.800 --> 00:17:45.420 align:middle line:84%
but now your own programs are
running in terms of how you're

00:17:45.420 --> 00:17:46.770 align:middle line:90%
interpreting these words.

00:17:46.770 --> 00:17:50.497 align:middle line:84%
So you may think you're giving
your full attention to someone,

00:17:50.497 --> 00:17:52.080 align:middle line:84%
and I've done the
same thing you have,

00:17:52.080 --> 00:17:54.090 align:middle line:84%
Ms. Smarty Pants, you
know, playing back.

00:17:54.090 --> 00:17:55.660 align:middle line:84%
I heard everything you
said, blah, blah, blah.

00:17:55.660 --> 00:17:56.790 align:middle line:84%
You want to hear what
you said before that?

00:17:56.790 --> 00:17:59.360 align:middle line:84%
Blah, blah, blah, you know, kind
of like if I were sitting here.

00:17:59.360 --> 00:17:59.984 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Right.

00:17:59.984 --> 00:18:02.180 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And that
does no good at all.

00:18:02.180 --> 00:18:04.980 align:middle line:84%
Because, in essence,
what you're doing

00:18:04.980 --> 00:18:08.630 align:middle line:84%
at that point in terms of
not only being defensive,

00:18:08.630 --> 00:18:10.960 align:middle line:84%
but this is a really
big one between couples,

00:18:10.960 --> 00:18:12.849 align:middle line:84%
you're really
trying to be right.

00:18:12.849 --> 00:18:13.390 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yes.

00:18:13.390 --> 00:18:17.650 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Let's talk about
what happens when either one

00:18:17.650 --> 00:18:20.260 align:middle line:90%
of the people has to be right.

00:18:20.260 --> 00:18:22.330 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Sometimes you
have to make a choice.

00:18:22.330 --> 00:18:25.680 align:middle line:84%
Do you want to be right or
do you want to be loved?

00:18:25.680 --> 00:18:27.800 align:middle line:84%
And often, for me,
in that situation,

00:18:27.800 --> 00:18:29.384 align:middle line:84%
it means I have to
keep my mouth shut.

00:18:29.384 --> 00:18:30.883 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And you
like being right.

00:18:30.883 --> 00:18:32.290 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: I love being right.

00:18:32.290 --> 00:18:33.580 align:middle line:90%
Of course.

00:18:33.580 --> 00:18:36.620 align:middle line:84%
I grew up in a home
where being right

00:18:36.620 --> 00:18:40.240 align:middle line:84%
was really the highest
value, like, really,

00:18:40.240 --> 00:18:43.230 align:middle line:84%
if you were right about
something, that was a big deal.

00:18:43.230 --> 00:18:46.890 align:middle line:84%
And I had to really
understand that being right

00:18:46.890 --> 00:18:50.780 align:middle line:84%
often means making
somebody else wrong.

00:18:50.780 --> 00:18:53.760 align:middle line:84%
And if we're going to win
together in a relationship,

00:18:53.760 --> 00:18:55.646 align:middle line:90%
then we both need to win.

00:18:55.646 --> 00:18:56.560 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:18:56.560 --> 00:19:01.050 align:middle line:84%
And that's a tough one
because this affects, I think,

00:19:01.050 --> 00:19:01.952 align:middle line:90%
most people.

00:19:01.952 --> 00:19:02.535 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yeah.

00:19:02.535 --> 00:19:05.130 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Most people want to
think they can walk away from

00:19:05.130 --> 00:19:07.750 align:middle line:84%
whatever the situation
is with a little dignity,

00:19:07.750 --> 00:19:10.630 align:middle line:84%
feeling like they
weren't a total idiot.

00:19:10.630 --> 00:19:13.050 align:middle line:84%
So anyway, I wanted to
bring that up because I

00:19:13.050 --> 00:19:15.180 align:middle line:84%
know that is-- that's
a big point that you

00:19:15.180 --> 00:19:17.696 align:middle line:84%
made in your book, is
the need to be right.

00:19:17.696 --> 00:19:19.570 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about-- let's
go back for a moment

00:19:19.570 --> 00:19:25.420 align:middle line:84%
to-- give us a little bit of
the more technical definitions

00:19:25.420 --> 00:19:28.620 align:middle line:84%
of these chemical cascades
and the phases we go through,

00:19:28.620 --> 00:19:31.800 align:middle line:84%
so people can see themselves
and their relationships in that.

00:19:31.800 --> 00:19:34.540 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: You know,
Dr. Helen Fisher,

00:19:34.540 --> 00:19:37.690 align:middle line:84%
who's one of the leading
researchers and anthropologists

00:19:37.690 --> 00:19:41.860 align:middle line:84%
on love, has sort of outlined
the whole phases of where you

00:19:41.860 --> 00:19:45.330 align:middle line:84%
have this infatuation,
and then you go into lust.

00:19:45.330 --> 00:19:48.220 align:middle line:84%
And then that's when all
the chemicals are going off.

00:19:48.220 --> 00:19:51.800 align:middle line:84%
And then, eventually,
you go into reality.

00:19:51.800 --> 00:19:53.560 align:middle line:84%
But what she's
been able to do is

00:19:53.560 --> 00:19:57.430 align:middle line:84%
she can take people and put
them in a CAT scan machine

00:19:57.430 --> 00:20:00.180 align:middle line:84%
and ask them questions
about their relationship.

00:20:00.180 --> 00:20:03.460 align:middle line:84%
And by looking at the CAT
scan, tell you whether or not

00:20:03.460 --> 00:20:06.570 align:middle line:84%
you're still in love, because
different parts of the brain

00:20:06.570 --> 00:20:08.090 align:middle line:90%
will light up.

00:20:08.090 --> 00:20:12.200 align:middle line:84%
The thing about that is that you
could be in the CAT scan today

00:20:12.200 --> 00:20:14.790 align:middle line:84%
and not be in love, but
she could retest you

00:20:14.790 --> 00:20:18.110 align:middle line:84%
in three months and you
could be in love again.

00:20:18.110 --> 00:20:23.557 align:middle line:84%
So that's why we can't trust our
feelings when it comes to love.

00:20:23.557 --> 00:20:25.140 align:middle line:84%
Somebody asked me
the other day, well,

00:20:25.140 --> 00:20:29.810 align:middle line:90%
how do I know if he loves me?

00:20:29.810 --> 00:20:33.480 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well, I can only
speak from my point of view,

00:20:33.480 --> 00:20:35.420 align:middle line:90%
how I know Brian loves me.

00:20:35.420 --> 00:20:39.500 align:middle line:84%
I know he loves me because
when I injure myself,

00:20:39.500 --> 00:20:41.590 align:middle line:84%
and I'm a klutz,
it happens often,

00:20:41.590 --> 00:20:44.100 align:middle line:84%
I can see the
concern in his eyes.

00:20:44.100 --> 00:20:46.570 align:middle line:84%
And he'll ask me
right away are you OK.

00:20:46.570 --> 00:20:48.790 align:middle line:84%
And he'll come and help me
off the floor or whatever

00:20:48.790 --> 00:20:50.600 align:middle line:90%
crazy thing that I've done.

00:20:50.600 --> 00:20:54.540 align:middle line:84%
Or if I'm having-- if I'm losing
it, which I do on occasion,

00:20:54.540 --> 00:20:57.930 align:middle line:84%
completely melt down and
lose it, he'll sit me down

00:20:57.930 --> 00:20:59.420 align:middle line:90%
and he'll hold my hands.

00:20:59.420 --> 00:21:01.870 align:middle line:84%
And he'll remind
me what I teach.

00:21:01.870 --> 00:21:04.690 align:middle line:90%
Oh, everything already is OK.

00:21:04.690 --> 00:21:06.790 align:middle line:84%
The problem's
already been solved.

00:21:06.790 --> 00:21:08.370 align:middle line:90%
We're in this together.

00:21:08.370 --> 00:21:11.310 align:middle line:84%
We're going to figure
this out together.

00:21:11.310 --> 00:21:14.350 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: That's a very
generous, loving gesture.

00:21:14.350 --> 00:21:15.130 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Exactly.

00:21:15.130 --> 00:21:17.110 align:middle line:84%
Now, for other
people, they don't

00:21:17.110 --> 00:21:18.500 align:middle line:84%
feel loved unless
they're getting

00:21:18.500 --> 00:21:22.920 align:middle line:84%
roses and candy and cards,
which is why I love that book,

00:21:22.920 --> 00:21:24.085 align:middle line:90%
"The Five Love Languages."

00:21:24.085 --> 00:21:24.710 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:21:24.710 --> 00:21:26.220 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Because everybody--

00:21:26.220 --> 00:21:27.130 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Shows it differently.

00:21:27.130 --> 00:21:28.005 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Differently.

00:21:28.005 --> 00:21:32.880 align:middle line:84%
Like, for me, if you are being
affectionate and touching me,

00:21:32.880 --> 00:21:34.910 align:middle line:90%
that's how I feel love.

00:21:34.910 --> 00:21:37.440 align:middle line:84%
I have other friends
that need gifts.

00:21:37.440 --> 00:21:41.110 align:middle line:84%
For Brian, it's acts of
service and affection.

00:21:41.110 --> 00:21:42.730 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: So it's a good fit.

00:21:42.730 --> 00:21:44.450 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Yeah, there's a
guy named Dr. Gary Chapman.

00:21:44.450 --> 00:21:46.616 align:middle line:10%
He wrote this great book,
"The Five Love Languages."

00:21:46.616 --> 00:21:49.980 align:middle line:10%
I highly recommend anybody
in any kind of relationship

00:21:49.980 --> 00:21:50.790 align:middle line:10%
read this book.

00:21:50.790 --> 00:21:52.840 align:middle line:90%
It's awesome.

00:21:52.840 --> 00:21:55.180 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And we look at
the difference between male

00:21:55.180 --> 00:21:57.130 align:middle line:84%
and female and what we
need from each other,

00:21:57.130 --> 00:22:01.260 align:middle line:84%
and one of the points you make
in your book is that men tend

00:22:01.260 --> 00:22:03.350 align:middle line:84%
to, and these are
blanket statements,

00:22:03.350 --> 00:22:08.260 align:middle line:84%
but tend to value being
respected by the woman even

00:22:08.260 --> 00:22:10.740 align:middle line:84%
more than being
loved by the woman.

00:22:10.740 --> 00:22:11.740 align:middle line:90%
Let's talk about that.

00:22:11.740 --> 00:22:17.160 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Yes, actually, men
crave respect more than sex.

00:22:17.160 --> 00:22:19.557 align:middle line:90%
And most women don't know that.

00:22:19.557 --> 00:22:20.140 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: No.

00:22:20.140 --> 00:22:23.260 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: They need respect
and they need appreciation.

00:22:23.260 --> 00:22:25.320 align:middle line:84%
And I had a really
funny conversation

00:22:25.320 --> 00:22:27.190 align:middle line:84%
with my hairdresser
the other day.

00:22:27.190 --> 00:22:28.950 align:middle line:84%
Because he was--
he's doing my hair

00:22:28.950 --> 00:22:31.810 align:middle line:84%
and I'm going off on book tour
and I tell him about the book.

00:22:31.810 --> 00:22:33.500 align:middle line:90%
And I know that he's divorced.

00:22:33.500 --> 00:22:37.530 align:middle line:84%
And I said to him why
did you get divorced?

00:22:37.530 --> 00:22:38.690 align:middle line:90%
He said car keys.

00:22:38.690 --> 00:22:40.222 align:middle line:90%
It's like what.

00:22:40.222 --> 00:22:41.310 align:middle line:90%
He said car keys.

00:22:41.310 --> 00:22:44.990 align:middle line:84%
Really, he said my wife and I
started this salon together,

00:22:44.990 --> 00:22:47.270 align:middle line:90%
but she used to leave before me.

00:22:47.270 --> 00:22:50.930 align:middle line:84%
And three out of seven days,
she would take my car keys

00:22:50.930 --> 00:22:54.080 align:middle line:84%
with her, which meant that I
had to be at the salon an hour

00:22:54.080 --> 00:22:57.780 align:middle line:84%
longer than necessary while she
brought me back my car keys.

00:22:57.780 --> 00:23:00.370 align:middle line:84%
And she would never
apologize, and she never

00:23:00.370 --> 00:23:02.470 align:middle line:84%
realized how
inconsiderate she was.

00:23:02.470 --> 00:23:05.770 align:middle line:84%
So, honestly, we got
divorced over car keys.

00:23:05.770 --> 00:23:08.750 align:middle line:84%
So then I said to him
tell me about the best

00:23:08.750 --> 00:23:10.530 align:middle line:90%
day of your marriage.

00:23:10.530 --> 00:23:13.740 align:middle line:84%
And he lights up, and he said
I can tell you every detail.

00:23:13.740 --> 00:23:17.350 align:middle line:84%
He goes we were three years
into having our business open.

00:23:17.350 --> 00:23:19.030 align:middle line:90%
We were driving on the 8.

00:23:19.030 --> 00:23:21.020 align:middle line:90%
We were near the Clairmont exit.

00:23:21.020 --> 00:23:22.700 align:middle line:84%
And she turned to
me and she said,

00:23:22.700 --> 00:23:25.500 align:middle line:90%
Tom, I am so proud of you.

00:23:25.500 --> 00:23:29.080 align:middle line:84%
You've done such a great job of
making our business a success.

00:23:29.080 --> 00:23:30.860 align:middle line:90%
And you are such a good dad.

00:23:30.860 --> 00:23:34.660 align:middle line:84%
And I know I don't say it often
enough, but I really love you.

00:23:34.660 --> 00:23:37.390 align:middle line:84%
And I said, OK, tell me about
the worst day of your marriage.

00:23:37.390 --> 00:23:39.740 align:middle line:84%
He said I remember
like it was yesterday.

00:23:39.740 --> 00:23:43.030 align:middle line:84%
We were driving down the 8, we
were in the exact same spot.

00:23:43.030 --> 00:23:46.190 align:middle line:84%
We were near the Clairmont
exit, and the recession

00:23:46.190 --> 00:23:47.360 align:middle line:90%
had just started.

00:23:47.360 --> 00:23:49.060 align:middle line:90%
And our business was failing.

00:23:49.060 --> 00:23:51.100 align:middle line:84%
And she was screaming
at me telling me

00:23:51.100 --> 00:23:54.270 align:middle line:84%
what an idiot I was that I
couldn't fix the business

00:23:54.270 --> 00:23:55.750 align:middle line:90%
in the middle of the recession.

00:23:55.750 --> 00:23:57.764 align:middle line:84%
And that was the
end of our marriage.

00:23:57.764 --> 00:23:58.430 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:23:58.430 --> 00:24:00.840 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: And I thought
what a telling story.

00:24:00.840 --> 00:24:03.810 align:middle line:84%
The thing he remembers
and values most

00:24:03.810 --> 00:24:07.510 align:middle line:84%
was the love and appreciation
and acknowledgement.

00:24:07.510 --> 00:24:09.460 align:middle line:84%
And the thing that
killed the marriage

00:24:09.460 --> 00:24:11.500 align:middle line:90%
was the lack of respect.

00:24:11.500 --> 00:24:12.950 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:24:12.950 --> 00:24:13.720 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:24:13.720 --> 00:24:15.940 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Because
men need to win.

00:24:15.940 --> 00:24:18.640 align:middle line:84%
And we need to set
them up to win.

00:24:18.640 --> 00:24:22.000 align:middle line:84%
And I-- and here's the thing
a lot of people don't know.

00:24:22.000 --> 00:24:26.850 align:middle line:84%
A man can't be happy
unless his woman's happy.

00:24:26.850 --> 00:24:28.880 align:middle line:84%
And I can hear the
women in the audience

00:24:28.880 --> 00:24:32.740 align:middle line:84%
saying but I tell them all the
time what I need to be happy.

00:24:32.740 --> 00:24:35.820 align:middle line:84%
And my answer to them is,
yes, and your shaming,

00:24:35.820 --> 00:24:38.910 align:middle line:84%
and blaming, screaming,
yelling, bitching, moaning.

00:24:38.910 --> 00:24:41.810 align:middle line:84%
And when you do that,
he's not listening.

00:24:41.810 --> 00:24:43.365 align:middle line:90%
He can't hear you.

00:24:43.365 --> 00:24:47.050 align:middle line:84%
You become mommy,
and he tunes you out.

00:24:47.050 --> 00:24:51.480 align:middle line:84%
But there is a way to get all
your needs and desires met,

00:24:51.480 --> 00:24:55.330 align:middle line:84%
but it requires a really
sweet tone of voice.

00:24:55.330 --> 00:24:59.250 align:middle line:84%
And you have to tell him what
it's going to provide for him.

00:24:59.250 --> 00:25:00.400 align:middle line:90%
So I have an example.

00:25:00.400 --> 00:25:02.525 align:middle line:84%
I have a story to share
about why this really work.

00:25:02.525 --> 00:25:04.550 align:middle line:84%
So I can't tell you
how many women tell me

00:25:04.550 --> 00:25:07.310 align:middle line:84%
the thing that drives them
nutty about their husband

00:25:07.310 --> 00:25:09.810 align:middle line:84%
is that they have
to constantly remind

00:25:09.810 --> 00:25:12.670 align:middle line:90%
them to take the trash out.

00:25:12.670 --> 00:25:15.210 align:middle line:84%
So here's how you get them
to take the trash out.

00:25:15.210 --> 00:25:17.790 align:middle line:84%
The next time he does
take the trash out,

00:25:17.790 --> 00:25:22.460 align:middle line:84%
even if you have to remind him,
when he walks back in the door,

00:25:22.460 --> 00:25:26.050 align:middle line:84%
walk over to him,
give him a big hug,

00:25:26.050 --> 00:25:30.040 align:middle line:84%
and then whisper in his
ear you are my hero.

00:25:30.040 --> 00:25:33.420 align:middle line:84%
I am so grateful to
you for taking out

00:25:33.420 --> 00:25:35.630 align:middle line:90%
that stinky, smelly trash.

00:25:35.630 --> 00:25:37.610 align:middle line:90%
I can't stand touching it.

00:25:37.610 --> 00:25:39.630 align:middle line:84%
You have no idea
what it does for me

00:25:39.630 --> 00:25:43.740 align:middle line:84%
and how sexy it is when
you take the trash out.

00:25:43.740 --> 00:25:46.250 align:middle line:84%
If you do that, he's
never ever going

00:25:46.250 --> 00:25:48.580 align:middle line:84%
to forget to take
the trash out again.

00:25:48.580 --> 00:25:51.370 align:middle line:90%
He just had this big win.

00:25:51.370 --> 00:25:54.370 align:middle line:84%
Now, the opposite to
that, the way women end up

00:25:54.370 --> 00:25:57.130 align:middle line:84%
really having men
lose all the time,

00:25:57.130 --> 00:25:59.510 align:middle line:84%
and this may come
as a surprise, is

00:25:59.510 --> 00:26:05.620 align:middle line:84%
that any time you put yourself
down to your guy, he's losing.

00:26:05.620 --> 00:26:06.470 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:26:06.470 --> 00:26:08.875 align:middle line:90%
Because he chose you.

00:26:08.875 --> 00:26:09.500 align:middle line:90%
And if you're--

00:26:09.500 --> 00:26:11.124 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: That
diminishes both of you.

00:26:11.124 --> 00:26:12.170 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yeah.

00:26:12.170 --> 00:26:14.300 align:middle line:84%
And you know, I've
got too many wrinkles.

00:26:14.300 --> 00:26:15.600 align:middle line:90%
I've got cellulite.

00:26:15.600 --> 00:26:17.610 align:middle line:90%
I need to lose 50 pounds.

00:26:17.610 --> 00:26:22.780 align:middle line:84%
And any way that you're making
yourself smaller, he's losing.

00:26:22.780 --> 00:26:24.250 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yeah,
that makes sense.

00:26:24.250 --> 00:26:29.210 align:middle line:84%
In fact, I did this little
pilot show on men and love.

00:26:29.210 --> 00:26:32.650 align:middle line:84%
And it was myself guiding
the panel of three men,

00:26:32.650 --> 00:26:34.480 align:middle line:90%
of different age groups.

00:26:34.480 --> 00:26:37.160 align:middle line:84%
One was from Europe, the
other two were American.

00:26:37.160 --> 00:26:40.870 align:middle line:84%
And what was interesting was
at the very end of the program,

00:26:40.870 --> 00:26:47.620 align:middle line:84%
I said what I think I'm hearing
here is that, in the end,

00:26:47.620 --> 00:26:53.976 align:middle line:84%
you-- it sounds like you need
women more than we need you.

00:26:53.976 --> 00:26:58.510 align:middle line:84%
And they were all say-- they
said almost simultaneously yes.

00:26:58.510 --> 00:27:01.119 align:middle line:90%
We're here to serve you.

00:27:01.119 --> 00:27:01.660 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yes.

00:27:01.660 --> 00:27:04.440 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And no one, I mean,
starting the conversation, A,

00:27:04.440 --> 00:27:06.380 align:middle line:90%
I wouldn't have suspected that.

00:27:06.380 --> 00:27:11.030 align:middle line:84%
And, again, this goes back
into the archetypal energy

00:27:11.030 --> 00:27:13.430 align:middle line:84%
of being the hero,
needing to be the hero,

00:27:13.430 --> 00:27:14.910 align:middle line:84%
or you wouldn't
incarnate as male.

00:27:14.910 --> 00:27:15.550 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Right.

00:27:15.550 --> 00:27:18.030 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Incarnate as a
female, if you don't need that.

00:27:18.030 --> 00:27:21.410 align:middle line:84%
And so, looking
along these lines,

00:27:21.410 --> 00:27:23.630 align:middle line:84%
if we're constantly
making someone wrong

00:27:23.630 --> 00:27:26.170 align:middle line:84%
and diminishing
ourselves, that takes away

00:27:26.170 --> 00:27:28.830 align:middle line:84%
the potential to be
the hero, which is

00:27:28.830 --> 00:27:30.920 align:middle line:90%
a very natural state of being.

00:27:30.920 --> 00:27:33.470 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Yeah, and the other
thing that a lot of women do is

00:27:33.470 --> 00:27:36.220 align:middle line:84%
they give too much, and
they don't raise the bar

00:27:36.220 --> 00:27:37.139 align:middle line:90%
for the guy.

00:27:37.139 --> 00:27:38.680 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: OK, let's
talk about that.

00:27:38.680 --> 00:27:42.210 align:middle line:84%
I tend to be kind of more in
that category of just flowing

00:27:42.210 --> 00:27:44.610 align:middle line:90%
energy out and being an enabler.

00:27:44.610 --> 00:27:47.960 align:middle line:84%
Oh, don't worry,
sweetie, it was tough.

00:27:47.960 --> 00:27:49.790 align:middle line:90%
Don't be so hard on yourself.

00:27:49.790 --> 00:27:50.460 align:middle line:90%
Wrong.

00:27:50.460 --> 00:27:53.060 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: No, they--
they want to win.

00:27:53.060 --> 00:27:55.000 align:middle line:90%
They want to prove themselves.

00:27:55.000 --> 00:27:56.830 align:middle line:84%
So you got to raise
the bar for them.

00:27:56.830 --> 00:27:58.770 align:middle line:90%
What could they do for you?

00:27:58.770 --> 00:28:00.295 align:middle line:90%
You know, and let them know.

00:28:00.295 --> 00:28:02.170 align:middle line:84%
And then, like I said,
it's the tone of voice

00:28:02.170 --> 00:28:03.760 align:middle line:84%
and it's the way
that you say it.

00:28:03.760 --> 00:28:07.930 align:middle line:84%
And you only want to make
one request at a time.

00:28:07.930 --> 00:28:10.032 align:middle line:90%
One, or one question at a time.

00:28:10.032 --> 00:28:11.615 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Don't lay
down a manifesto.

00:28:11.615 --> 00:28:14.040 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Right/
We can multitask.

00:28:14.040 --> 00:28:15.950 align:middle line:84%
We can handle multiple
things at a time.

00:28:15.950 --> 00:28:16.690 align:middle line:90%
They can not.

00:28:16.690 --> 00:28:18.560 align:middle line:84%
Their brains are
wired differently.

00:28:18.560 --> 00:28:22.500 align:middle line:84%
So if you have a question, ask
one question and then shut up

00:28:22.500 --> 00:28:25.980 align:middle line:84%
and give them all the time they
need to answer the question.

00:28:25.980 --> 00:28:30.880 align:middle line:84%
Or if you have a request,
make one very clear request

00:28:30.880 --> 00:28:32.970 align:middle line:84%
that they can think
about and answer.

00:28:32.970 --> 00:28:33.910 align:middle line:90%
Or you can tell them.

00:28:33.910 --> 00:28:35.409 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to
tell me right now.

00:28:35.409 --> 00:28:37.030 align:middle line:84%
You could tell me
in a couple of days.

00:28:37.030 --> 00:28:39.600 align:middle line:84%
But I'm really thinking it might
be fun next weakened that we

00:28:39.600 --> 00:28:42.000 align:middle line:90%
go skiing up in snow mass.

00:28:42.000 --> 00:28:44.330 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: But don't overwhelm
someone with your list.

00:28:44.330 --> 00:28:45.090 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Right.

00:28:45.090 --> 00:28:47.330 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And no less
in a nasty tone of voice

00:28:47.330 --> 00:28:48.460 align:middle line:90%
or a blaming tone of voice.

00:28:48.460 --> 00:28:49.960 align:middle line:84%
It's going to kill
the relationship.

00:28:49.960 --> 00:28:51.530 align:middle line:90%
So I think we've got that part.

00:28:51.530 --> 00:28:55.460 align:middle line:84%
Now, you also say that a woman
cannot expect a man to know

00:28:55.460 --> 00:28:58.710 align:middle line:84%
what her needs are, just
intuit what her needs are.

00:28:58.710 --> 00:29:00.525 align:middle line:90%
He's focused on what he's doing.

00:29:00.525 --> 00:29:01.150 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Right.

00:29:01.150 --> 00:29:03.691 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And you talk about
a woman named Elizabeth who was

00:29:03.691 --> 00:29:05.720 align:middle line:84%
proactive and wrote
her own user's manual,

00:29:05.720 --> 00:29:07.607 align:middle line:84%
which I think is
a brilliant idea.

00:29:07.607 --> 00:29:08.190 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yeah.

00:29:08.190 --> 00:29:12.790 align:middle line:84%
Because for her, love meant
getting lots of little cards,

00:29:12.790 --> 00:29:14.960 align:middle line:90%
and flowers, and candies.

00:29:14.960 --> 00:29:18.280 align:middle line:84%
And even though her husband
told her all the time

00:29:18.280 --> 00:29:21.790 align:middle line:84%
that he loved her, she
needed this demonstration.

00:29:21.790 --> 00:29:23.820 align:middle line:84%
So she eventually
wrote, you know,

00:29:23.820 --> 00:29:27.040 align:middle line:84%
the owner's manual for Elizabeth
on how to make her happy.

00:29:27.040 --> 00:29:29.010 align:middle line:84%
And then she said
very specifically put

00:29:29.010 --> 00:29:33.490 align:middle line:84%
in there what kind of flower
she wanted, what kind of candy.

00:29:33.490 --> 00:29:35.200 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: This was
super proactive.

00:29:35.200 --> 00:29:38.060 align:middle line:10%
>> FORD: So that-- because he
did want to make her happy,

00:29:38.060 --> 00:29:41.670 align:middle line:10%
but how would he know that
tulips were her favorite,

00:29:41.670 --> 00:29:44.920 align:middle line:10%
and that she particularly
liked red and purple tulips,

00:29:44.920 --> 00:29:46.560 align:middle line:10%
or whatever it was.

00:29:46.560 --> 00:29:48.770 align:middle line:90%
So she got very specific.

00:29:48.770 --> 00:29:50.610 align:middle line:90%
So I think that's a great idea.

00:29:50.610 --> 00:29:53.490 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And what about in the
notion of the beginning of what

00:29:53.490 --> 00:29:57.040 align:middle line:84%
looks like it could be a-- I
don't like the word serious--

00:29:57.040 --> 00:29:59.980 align:middle line:90%
but a lasting relationship.

00:29:59.980 --> 00:30:02.440 align:middle line:84%
What if everybody
was proactive enough

00:30:02.440 --> 00:30:06.590 align:middle line:84%
to say-- to present
the other one with,

00:30:06.590 --> 00:30:08.200 align:middle line:84%
as you say, like
a user's manual,

00:30:08.200 --> 00:30:10.950 align:middle line:84%
saying this is where
I really trip up,

00:30:10.950 --> 00:30:13.230 align:middle line:84%
and this is what
hurts my feelings.

00:30:13.230 --> 00:30:15.170 align:middle line:84%
This is what makes
me feel great.

00:30:15.170 --> 00:30:17.520 align:middle line:84%
And so you had the advantage
of that knowledge--

00:30:17.520 --> 00:30:20.700 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Well, I actually wrote
that book and I give it away

00:30:20.700 --> 00:30:23.330 align:middle line:90%
for free as a bonus package.

00:30:23.330 --> 00:30:27.222 align:middle line:10%
If you buy this book and you
go to MatetoSoulmate.com,

00:30:27.222 --> 00:30:29.590 align:middle line:10%
you can download "The
Everything Book."

00:30:29.590 --> 00:30:31.430 align:middle line:84%
And "The Everything
Book" is a fill

00:30:31.430 --> 00:30:34.880 align:middle line:84%
in the blank book for couples
to fill out and exchange,

00:30:34.880 --> 00:30:36.740 align:middle line:84%
so you have all
this information.

00:30:36.740 --> 00:30:38.290 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I think
it's a great idea,

00:30:38.290 --> 00:30:41.030 align:middle line:84%
to instead of just shooting
in the dark and each hoping

00:30:41.030 --> 00:30:43.540 align:middle line:84%
the other one perceives
things correctly.

00:30:43.540 --> 00:30:46.100 align:middle line:90%
It's a crap shoot that way.

00:30:46.100 --> 00:30:50.260 align:middle line:84%
And we're all filtering
the information

00:30:50.260 --> 00:30:52.390 align:middle line:84%
through our own lens
of experience, which

00:30:52.390 --> 00:30:53.862 align:middle line:84%
you can say one
thing, but you're

00:30:53.862 --> 00:30:55.820 align:middle line:84%
interpreting-- you're
interpreting what they're

00:30:55.820 --> 00:30:56.944 align:middle line:90%
saying totally differently.

00:30:56.944 --> 00:30:58.123 align:middle line:90%
So it's very confusing.

00:30:58.123 --> 00:30:58.914 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: It can be.

00:30:58.914 --> 00:30:59.700 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: In the beginning.

00:30:59.700 --> 00:31:01.690 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: But that's sort of
the point and the purpose

00:31:01.690 --> 00:31:02.481 align:middle line:90%
of the whole thing.

00:31:02.481 --> 00:31:07.450 align:middle line:10%
So Harville Hendrix believes
that we have a built in mate

00:31:07.450 --> 00:31:10.660 align:middle line:10%
selector and that
it's not random

00:31:10.660 --> 00:31:13.220 align:middle line:10%
that we run into our
soulmate, that we actually

00:31:13.220 --> 00:31:17.340 align:middle line:10%
pick the perfect person for us
who's going to have the owner's

00:31:17.340 --> 00:31:20.520 align:middle line:10%
manual to all the buttons
to all our childhood

00:31:20.520 --> 00:31:25.090 align:middle line:10%
wounds, to bring them up, so
we can become whole and healed.

00:31:25.090 --> 00:31:29.670 align:middle line:84%
And he says that's the
real purpose of marriage,

00:31:29.670 --> 00:31:31.850 align:middle line:90%
that it's absolutely normal.

00:31:31.850 --> 00:31:34.320 align:middle line:84%
And yet, we live
like, oh, when there's

00:31:34.320 --> 00:31:36.370 align:middle line:84%
bumps in the road
in the relationship,

00:31:36.370 --> 00:31:37.432 align:middle line:90%
that something's wrong.

00:31:37.432 --> 00:31:38.140 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:31:38.140 --> 00:31:40.510 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: When the
reality is, it's normal.

00:31:40.510 --> 00:31:41.350 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:31:41.350 --> 00:31:43.620 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about
Jill Mangino's story.

00:31:43.620 --> 00:31:47.640 align:middle line:84%
Because we're going
to talk-- I love

00:31:47.640 --> 00:31:49.170 align:middle line:90%
learning by way of example.

00:31:49.170 --> 00:31:51.760 align:middle line:84%
And I thought that was
just a fascinating story.

00:31:51.760 --> 00:31:52.787 align:middle line:90%
She's a lovely lady.

00:31:52.787 --> 00:31:53.370 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yeah.

00:31:53.370 --> 00:31:55.750 align:middle line:90%
So Jill's a good friend of mine.

00:31:55.750 --> 00:31:59.650 align:middle line:84%
And she had many
long-term relationships

00:31:59.650 --> 00:32:02.220 align:middle line:84%
with guys that
were just like her.

00:32:02.220 --> 00:32:04.510 align:middle line:84%
They wore organic
cotton clothing,

00:32:04.510 --> 00:32:07.280 align:middle line:84%
and they did yoga every
day, and juice fasts,

00:32:07.280 --> 00:32:08.710 align:middle line:90%
and they were vegans.

00:32:08.710 --> 00:32:11.230 align:middle line:84%
And they were very
difficult relationships

00:32:11.230 --> 00:32:13.170 align:middle line:90%
and never made her happy.

00:32:13.170 --> 00:32:16.470 align:middle line:84%
Finally, she moved back to
her hometown in New Jersey.

00:32:16.470 --> 00:32:19.240 align:middle line:84%
She went to her 20 year
high school reunion.

00:32:19.240 --> 00:32:22.130 align:middle line:84%
She ran into her high
school boyfriend, Ray.

00:32:22.130 --> 00:32:23.750 align:middle line:90%
And they started dating.

00:32:23.750 --> 00:32:26.800 align:middle line:84%
And then they fell in love, and
then they moved in together,

00:32:26.800 --> 00:32:29.960 align:middle line:84%
and then he proposed,
and she took the ring.

00:32:29.960 --> 00:32:32.070 align:middle line:84%
So every time I
would talk to her

00:32:32.070 --> 00:32:34.070 align:middle line:90%
I would say when's the wedding?

00:32:34.070 --> 00:32:36.420 align:middle line:84%
And for the first four,
years she would say, oh,

00:32:36.420 --> 00:32:37.390 align:middle line:90%
I'm just too busy.

00:32:37.390 --> 00:32:38.480 align:middle line:90%
We haven't planned it yet.

00:32:38.480 --> 00:32:39.350 align:middle line:90%
There's no rush.

00:32:39.350 --> 00:32:42.270 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, let's
talk about Ray's reality

00:32:42.270 --> 00:32:42.990 align:middle line:90%
and personality.

00:32:42.990 --> 00:32:44.010 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: I'm going to get there.

00:32:44.010 --> 00:32:44.510 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:32:44.510 --> 00:32:45.530 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: All right.

00:32:45.530 --> 00:32:48.300 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: After the fourth
year, I said to her tell me

00:32:48.300 --> 00:32:50.200 align:middle line:90%
what's really going on.

00:32:50.200 --> 00:32:52.520 align:middle line:84%
You can't tell me you've
been so busy for four years

00:32:52.520 --> 00:32:54.950 align:middle line:84%
that you couldn't
plan a wedding.

00:32:54.950 --> 00:32:57.880 align:middle line:84%
She said Ray's not
spiritual enough.

00:32:57.880 --> 00:32:59.930 align:middle line:84%
I said, well, what
do you mean by that.

00:32:59.930 --> 00:33:03.740 align:middle line:84%
She said, well, you know, I'm a
vegan chanting yoga green juice

00:33:03.740 --> 00:33:05.040 align:middle line:90%
fasting kind of girl.

00:33:05.040 --> 00:33:06.860 align:middle line:90%
Yes, I know all about you.

00:33:06.860 --> 00:33:08.600 align:middle line:84%
Well, what you
don't know about Ray

00:33:08.600 --> 00:33:11.470 align:middle line:84%
is that he repairs
motorcycles for a living.

00:33:11.470 --> 00:33:12.690 align:middle line:90%
He smokes cigarettes.

00:33:12.690 --> 00:33:13.990 align:middle line:90%
He smokes pot.

00:33:13.990 --> 00:33:14.840 align:middle line:90%
He's a meat eater.

00:33:14.840 --> 00:33:17.480 align:middle line:90%
He actually hunts all the time.

00:33:17.480 --> 00:33:19.570 align:middle line:84%
And he doesn't
meditate, and he doesn't

00:33:19.570 --> 00:33:21.670 align:middle line:90%
read Deepak Chopra books.

00:33:21.670 --> 00:33:25.190 align:middle line:90%
And it's just not a good fit.

00:33:25.190 --> 00:33:27.650 align:middle line:84%
Well, eventually, she
broke up with him.

00:33:27.650 --> 00:33:29.947 align:middle line:84%
But because the
recession had hit,

00:33:29.947 --> 00:33:31.280 align:middle line:90%
they were still living together.

00:33:31.280 --> 00:33:33.090 align:middle line:84%
They couldn't
afford to move out.

00:33:33.090 --> 00:33:35.590 align:middle line:84%
And at one point, she
got very, very sick.

00:33:35.590 --> 00:33:38.240 align:middle line:84%
And he took very,
very good care of her.

00:33:38.240 --> 00:33:40.600 align:middle line:84%
And after she got better,
she was in the kitchen

00:33:40.600 --> 00:33:45.140 align:middle line:84%
one morning making her chia
seed gruel with almond milk

00:33:45.140 --> 00:33:48.460 align:middle line:84%
that she does, and he walks
in through the back door

00:33:48.460 --> 00:33:50.670 align:middle line:84%
with a bunch of dead
turkeys, and his hunting

00:33:50.670 --> 00:33:53.710 align:middle line:84%
dog, and his rifle,
and his camo wear.

00:33:53.710 --> 00:33:56.990 align:middle line:84%
And she says to him, oh,
hi, how was your morning.

00:33:56.990 --> 00:33:59.670 align:middle line:84%
And he said to her,
oh, it was beautiful.

00:33:59.670 --> 00:34:02.945 align:middle line:84%
I was walking through the
forest as the sun was filtering

00:34:02.945 --> 00:34:05.320 align:middle line:84%
through the leaves, and I
could hear the leaves crunching

00:34:05.320 --> 00:34:06.210 align:middle line:90%
under my boots.

00:34:06.210 --> 00:34:10.440 align:middle line:84%
And it was just a really
magnificent, divine morning.

00:34:10.440 --> 00:34:12.530 align:middle line:84%
And Jill's thinking
to yourself, wow, that

00:34:12.530 --> 00:34:14.699 align:middle line:90%
even sounds kind of spiritual.

00:34:14.699 --> 00:34:16.280 align:middle line:90%
And then she forgot about it.

00:34:16.280 --> 00:34:18.860 align:middle line:84%
And then later that day,
he came home from work.

00:34:18.860 --> 00:34:20.719 align:middle line:90%
And he was in tears.

00:34:20.719 --> 00:34:22.409 align:middle line:90%
She's like what's the matter.

00:34:22.409 --> 00:34:24.100 align:middle line:90%
And he said Bob died.

00:34:24.100 --> 00:34:27.630 align:middle line:84%
Bob was his boss, the owner
of the motorcycle repair shop.

00:34:27.630 --> 00:34:29.630 align:middle line:84%
And he was really
upset about it.

00:34:29.630 --> 00:34:32.179 align:middle line:84%
And he said the
funeral's in two days.

00:34:32.179 --> 00:34:34.699 align:middle line:84%
And he goes you know how
socially phobic I can be.

00:34:34.699 --> 00:34:35.710 align:middle line:90%
Will you go with me?

00:34:35.710 --> 00:34:38.179 align:middle line:84%
And she said, yes, of course,
I'll go to the funeral.

00:34:38.179 --> 00:34:39.540 align:middle line:90%
So they go to the funeral.

00:34:39.540 --> 00:34:41.960 align:middle line:84%
There's 300 people
there, mostly bikers

00:34:41.960 --> 00:34:45.500 align:middle line:90%
in leather jackets, that crowd.

00:34:45.500 --> 00:34:48.440 align:middle line:90%
And the minister gives a eulogy.

00:34:48.440 --> 00:34:50.639 align:middle line:84%
And when he's done,
he says, is there

00:34:50.639 --> 00:34:53.239 align:middle line:84%
anybody who would like
to come up and say

00:34:53.239 --> 00:34:55.449 align:middle line:90%
a few words about Bob?

00:34:55.449 --> 00:34:59.020 align:middle line:84%
Nobody room-- nobody
moves, dead silence.

00:34:59.020 --> 00:35:00.830 align:middle line:84%
And all of a
sudden, Ray gets up,

00:35:00.830 --> 00:35:06.030 align:middle line:84%
socially phobic Ray gets up,
walks to the front of the room,

00:35:06.030 --> 00:35:10.020 align:middle line:84%
and he starts talking about
what a good man Bob was,

00:35:10.020 --> 00:35:13.590 align:middle line:84%
what a good father, a good
husband, a good community

00:35:13.590 --> 00:35:17.550 align:middle line:84%
citizen, what a good
boss, what a good friend.

00:35:17.550 --> 00:35:20.370 align:middle line:90%
And Jill starts to cry.

00:35:20.370 --> 00:35:23.310 align:middle line:84%
And she falls in love
with Ray all over again.

00:35:23.310 --> 00:35:25.970 align:middle line:84%
And she realizes
that she has been

00:35:25.970 --> 00:35:29.590 align:middle line:84%
the spiritually arrogant one,
that she's been judging him

00:35:29.590 --> 00:35:33.160 align:middle line:84%
by this criteria,
when, in fact, here

00:35:33.160 --> 00:35:36.920 align:middle line:84%
is this open-hearted generous
man who's been treating her

00:35:36.920 --> 00:35:41.690 align:middle line:84%
like a queen for years
and she's been judging him

00:35:41.690 --> 00:35:45.800 align:middle line:84%
because he hunts, and he
smokes, and he rides bikes,

00:35:45.800 --> 00:35:48.000 align:middle line:90%
and he doesn't do juice fasts.

00:35:48.000 --> 00:35:50.580 align:middle line:84%
So they are now very
happily married.

00:35:50.580 --> 00:35:53.070 align:middle line:84%
And I'm so glad to
report that when

00:35:53.070 --> 00:35:57.420 align:middle line:84%
I ask Jill the other day who's
your guru, she said to me

00:35:57.420 --> 00:35:59.100 align:middle line:90%
Ray's my guru.

00:35:59.100 --> 00:36:00.110 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: I love it.

00:36:00.110 --> 00:36:02.210 align:middle line:84%
And, you know, this
brings up a good point.

00:36:02.210 --> 00:36:08.750 align:middle line:84%
Ever since the addition of
new age culture to society,

00:36:08.750 --> 00:36:11.349 align:middle line:84%
it seems to have almost
created a greater divide.

00:36:11.349 --> 00:36:11.890 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yes.

00:36:11.890 --> 00:36:15.040 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: It hasn't done
what it was supposed to do,

00:36:15.040 --> 00:36:17.400 align:middle line:84%
which is to create
bridges to one another.

00:36:17.400 --> 00:36:20.074 align:middle line:84%
It's created a tremendous
amount of spiritual arrogance.

00:36:20.074 --> 00:36:20.990 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: And judgment.

00:36:20.990 --> 00:36:21.990 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: And judgment.

00:36:21.990 --> 00:36:25.340 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: And the truth is
men experience and express

00:36:25.340 --> 00:36:28.220 align:middle line:84%
spirituality
differently than we do.

00:36:28.220 --> 00:36:31.310 align:middle line:84%
So we may want to sit in the
Mile High Church or the Unity

00:36:31.310 --> 00:36:33.280 align:middle line:90%
Church and read certain books.

00:36:33.280 --> 00:36:36.150 align:middle line:84%
And if your guy is
coaching Little League

00:36:36.150 --> 00:36:40.490 align:middle line:84%
in volunteering at Big Brothers
and helping your mother get

00:36:40.490 --> 00:36:42.810 align:middle line:84%
in and out of the
car, and just being

00:36:42.810 --> 00:36:45.980 align:middle line:84%
an all around good
human being, what could

00:36:45.980 --> 00:36:47.930 align:middle line:90%
be more spiritual than that?

00:36:47.930 --> 00:36:49.350 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Exactly.

00:36:49.350 --> 00:36:51.400 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: And yet, when
I talk to single women,

00:36:51.400 --> 00:36:54.050 align:middle line:84%
the first thing they say is, oh,
well, I want a spiritual guy.

00:36:54.050 --> 00:36:55.549 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I've
heard this so often.

00:36:55.549 --> 00:36:58.420 align:middle line:84%
And most of those people
actually are alone.

00:36:58.420 --> 00:36:59.470 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yes.

00:36:59.470 --> 00:37:01.790 align:middle line:84%
They're alone with
their conversations

00:37:01.790 --> 00:37:05.040 align:middle line:84%
with God books, and their
workbooks, and their practices,

00:37:05.040 --> 00:37:06.160 align:middle line:90%
and their chanting.

00:37:06.160 --> 00:37:08.270 align:middle line:84%
I had this conversation
with Elizabeth Gilbert,

00:37:08.270 --> 00:37:09.950 align:middle line:90%
who wrote "Eat, Pray, Love."

00:37:09.950 --> 00:37:13.550 align:middle line:84%
And I said to her what do you
love most about your husband.

00:37:13.550 --> 00:37:15.210 align:middle line:84%
And she said, well,
my history was

00:37:15.210 --> 00:37:18.450 align:middle line:84%
to be with guys who would go
to meditation retreats with me.

00:37:18.450 --> 00:37:19.170 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:37:19.170 --> 00:37:22.470 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: She said but my husband
is never going to do yoga.

00:37:22.470 --> 00:37:24.140 align:middle line:90%
He's never going to meditate.

00:37:24.140 --> 00:37:26.840 align:middle line:84%
He's certainly never
doing a green juice fast.

00:37:26.840 --> 00:37:30.060 align:middle line:84%
But when I walk into
a room, his eyes

00:37:30.060 --> 00:37:32.510 align:middle line:84%
light up like it's
Christmas morning.

00:37:32.510 --> 00:37:35.930 align:middle line:84%
And he takes me by the hand
and leads me into the kitchen.

00:37:35.930 --> 00:37:39.290 align:middle line:84%
And he puts my feet up and
he hands me a glass of wine

00:37:39.290 --> 00:37:42.680 align:middle line:90%
and then he cooks me dinner.

00:37:42.680 --> 00:37:44.470 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: That's divine, right?

00:37:44.470 --> 00:37:45.620 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: And she's happy.

00:37:45.620 --> 00:37:49.730 align:middle line:84%
And she understands that she
is a meditating, chanting,

00:37:49.730 --> 00:37:52.320 align:middle line:84%
green juice fasting
kind of girl.

00:37:52.320 --> 00:37:53.660 align:middle line:90%
And he is not.

00:37:53.660 --> 00:37:54.790 align:middle line:90%
But he loves her.

00:37:54.790 --> 00:37:56.540 align:middle line:90%
He's devoted to her.

00:37:56.540 --> 00:37:58.270 align:middle line:90%
He's crazy about her.

00:37:58.270 --> 00:38:00.330 align:middle line:90%
And who wouldn't want that?

00:38:00.330 --> 00:38:04.350 align:middle line:84%
And yet, by most people
standards, is he spiritual?

00:38:04.350 --> 00:38:07.880 align:middle line:84%
Well, yes, in his own way,
because he puts all that love

00:38:07.880 --> 00:38:11.230 align:middle line:84%
in the food which he feeds
to her to nourish her body

00:38:11.230 --> 00:38:11.870 align:middle line:90%
and soul.

00:38:11.870 --> 00:38:14.200 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I'm to the point
where I can barely stand

00:38:14.200 --> 00:38:15.910 align:middle line:90%
to hear that word anymore.

00:38:15.910 --> 00:38:17.579 align:middle line:90%
Are you a spiritual person?

00:38:17.579 --> 00:38:18.370 align:middle line:90%
Well, you're alive.

00:38:18.370 --> 00:38:19.578 align:middle line:90%
You're walking on the planet.

00:38:19.578 --> 00:38:21.510 align:middle line:90%
You have passions and loves.

00:38:21.510 --> 00:38:23.910 align:middle line:84%
Yes, we don't need to
be asking that question.

00:38:23.910 --> 00:38:27.350 align:middle line:84%
But to define it so narrowly,
to, as you say, chanting,

00:38:27.350 --> 00:38:29.630 align:middle line:84%
and yoga, and green
juice fasting,

00:38:29.630 --> 00:38:33.060 align:middle line:84%
is really-- I'm
finding it quite trite.

00:38:33.060 --> 00:38:35.250 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Well, and
what I've noticed,

00:38:35.250 --> 00:38:37.950 align:middle line:84%
and what the people
who do all that,

00:38:37.950 --> 00:38:41.170 align:middle line:84%
what they don't understand is
if you're sitting in judgment

00:38:41.170 --> 00:38:44.470 align:middle line:84%
of somebody else, if you're
having toxic thoughts,

00:38:44.470 --> 00:38:45.859 align:middle line:90%
that is canceling out--

00:38:45.859 --> 00:38:46.650 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: You bet.

00:38:46.650 --> 00:38:49.120 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: All the vegan
food, and the chanting,

00:38:49.120 --> 00:38:50.510 align:middle line:90%
and the yoga that you're doing.

00:38:50.510 --> 00:38:51.400 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Exactly.

00:38:51.400 --> 00:38:54.510 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: It's better to sit
there and eat a pound of bacon

00:38:54.510 --> 00:38:58.040 align:middle line:84%
every day and have
loving kindness thoughts

00:38:58.040 --> 00:38:58.850 align:middle line:90%
for the world.

00:38:58.850 --> 00:38:59.660 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:38:59.660 --> 00:39:02.620 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: And yet we live like,
no, I'm going to live a nice,

00:39:02.620 --> 00:39:06.250 align:middle line:84%
long life if only
I do X, Y, and Z.

00:39:06.250 --> 00:39:09.820 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So we need a new
view of that, a reality check.

00:39:09.820 --> 00:39:11.880 align:middle line:84%
We've gone too far
one way and now we

00:39:11.880 --> 00:39:14.360 align:middle line:84%
have to go back and find
this point of equilibrium

00:39:14.360 --> 00:39:16.504 align:middle line:90%
where we really are a bridge.

00:39:16.504 --> 00:39:17.920 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: And what's
right for you.

00:39:17.920 --> 00:39:18.490 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: That's right.

00:39:18.490 --> 00:39:20.620 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: You know, being a
vegan may be right for you.

00:39:20.620 --> 00:39:21.330 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Exactly,
nothing wrong with that.

00:39:21.330 --> 00:39:22.470 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: It's not right for me.

00:39:22.470 --> 00:39:23.960 align:middle line:84%
I've tried it,
doesn't work for me.

00:39:23.960 --> 00:39:26.220 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, I did try it
and I almost died, you know.

00:39:26.220 --> 00:39:27.870 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I was a
vegetarian for 20 years

00:39:27.870 --> 00:39:29.620 align:middle line:84%
and started having lot
of health problems.

00:39:29.620 --> 00:39:32.340 align:middle line:84%
And I was very judgmental
about meat eating and all that.

00:39:32.340 --> 00:39:35.850 align:middle line:84%
And then I go back to becoming
essentially a carnivore

00:39:35.850 --> 00:39:37.920 align:middle line:90%
to support my own health again.

00:39:37.920 --> 00:39:39.940 align:middle line:84%
I'm embarrassed
initially, but then I

00:39:39.940 --> 00:39:42.540 align:middle line:90%
realized how arrogant I was.

00:39:42.540 --> 00:39:46.170 align:middle line:84%
And I was doing it only for
my own spiritual reasons.

00:39:46.170 --> 00:39:48.460 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't even doing
it for my health.

00:39:48.460 --> 00:39:52.650 align:middle line:84%
And I've been every which
way around the circle

00:39:52.650 --> 00:39:53.480 align:middle line:90%
on this journey.

00:39:53.480 --> 00:39:56.570 align:middle line:84%
And I see my own
arrogance in times past,

00:39:56.570 --> 00:39:58.780 align:middle line:90%
and even today, in certain ways.

00:39:58.780 --> 00:40:02.492 align:middle line:84%
And I think we've got to
start loving one another.

00:40:02.492 --> 00:40:03.450 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: And ourselves.

00:40:03.450 --> 00:40:04.491 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: And ourselves.

00:40:04.491 --> 00:40:07.420 align:middle line:84%
And quit trying to be
this idealized version

00:40:07.420 --> 00:40:09.330 align:middle line:90%
of a spiritual being.

00:40:09.330 --> 00:40:10.220 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Right.

00:40:10.220 --> 00:40:11.170 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:40:11.170 --> 00:40:14.000 align:middle line:90%
So now let's go to past lives.

00:40:14.000 --> 00:40:16.450 align:middle line:84%
How do you-- how
do you define it

00:40:16.450 --> 00:40:18.180 align:middle line:84%
when someone has
recognized someone

00:40:18.180 --> 00:40:20.310 align:middle line:90%
from a past life scenario?

00:40:20.310 --> 00:40:24.080 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Well, I-- I believe
that the past, the present,

00:40:24.080 --> 00:40:26.780 align:middle line:84%
and the future are all
happening right now.

00:40:26.780 --> 00:40:29.010 align:middle line:84%
So we can talk about
it as a past life,

00:40:29.010 --> 00:40:31.430 align:middle line:84%
but it's really more
like a parallel life.

00:40:31.430 --> 00:40:34.860 align:middle line:84%
But as we talked about
earlier, we have a tribe

00:40:34.860 --> 00:40:38.780 align:middle line:84%
and we have recognition when
we connect with our tribe.

00:40:38.780 --> 00:40:40.680 align:middle line:84%
And I do believe
when we're planning

00:40:40.680 --> 00:40:44.690 align:middle line:84%
to hook up in a particular
lifetime with a soulmate

00:40:44.690 --> 00:40:48.540 align:middle line:84%
that we go to a place that
they call recognition school

00:40:48.540 --> 00:40:51.790 align:middle line:84%
and we plan out the coincidences
and the synchronicities,

00:40:51.790 --> 00:40:54.530 align:middle line:84%
so that we can
recognize each other.

00:40:54.530 --> 00:40:59.100 align:middle line:84%
We can fall into nature's
trick and be crazy in love

00:40:59.100 --> 00:40:59.980 align:middle line:90%
and see this.

00:40:59.980 --> 00:41:02.730 align:middle line:84%
So that we can get
together and grow and heal

00:41:02.730 --> 00:41:05.250 align:middle line:90%
each other as a couple.

00:41:05.250 --> 00:41:07.890 align:middle line:84%
So I think that's an
important piece of it.

00:41:07.890 --> 00:41:10.980 align:middle line:84%
And you do not have to
believe in any of this

00:41:10.980 --> 00:41:12.892 align:middle line:90%
to manifest a soulmate.

00:41:12.892 --> 00:41:13.600 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:41:13.600 --> 00:41:14.387 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:41:14.387 --> 00:41:15.970 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: It's just
my personal belief.

00:41:15.970 --> 00:41:16.690 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:41:16.690 --> 00:41:20.500 align:middle line:84%
Now, I want to-- I was going
to have you tell me-- tell us

00:41:20.500 --> 00:41:22.944 align:middle line:84%
about Donna Eden
and her mate, but I

00:41:22.944 --> 00:41:25.110 align:middle line:84%
want to get into some of
the more functional aspects

00:41:25.110 --> 00:41:25.410 align:middle line:90%
of this.

00:41:25.410 --> 00:41:27.076 align:middle line:84%
If we have time, we'll
go back to Donna.

00:41:27.076 --> 00:41:30.100 align:middle line:84%
Because what she and her
husband David represented

00:41:30.100 --> 00:41:32.080 align:middle line:90%
is irreconcilable differences.

00:41:32.080 --> 00:41:32.750 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yes.

00:41:32.750 --> 00:41:37.290 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And there are many
reasons people come together.

00:41:37.290 --> 00:41:41.020 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes they come together
to create or produce something,

00:41:41.020 --> 00:41:43.890 align:middle line:84%
whether it's a child,
whether it's a pottery shop,

00:41:43.890 --> 00:41:46.570 align:middle line:90%
and spiritual school, whatever.

00:41:46.570 --> 00:41:48.130 align:middle line:84%
They're here for
purpose together.

00:41:48.130 --> 00:41:50.520 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't mean it's going
to be the easiest ride.

00:41:50.520 --> 00:41:52.350 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Well, there's
a guy named Dr.

00:41:52.350 --> 00:41:55.320 align:middle line:10%
John Gottman who's a marriage
researcher at the University

00:41:55.320 --> 00:41:56.680 align:middle line:10%
of Washington.

00:41:56.680 --> 00:41:58.470 align:middle line:10%
And he's just a total genius.

00:41:58.470 --> 00:42:03.100 align:middle line:10%
He's actually-- he can observe
any couple for 15 minutes

00:42:03.100 --> 00:42:07.200 align:middle line:10%
and tell you within 93%
accuracy whether or not they'll

00:42:07.200 --> 00:42:08.580 align:middle line:10%
be divorced in three years.

00:42:08.580 --> 00:42:09.440 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:42:09.440 --> 00:42:12.930 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: And what his studies
have found is that every

00:42:12.930 --> 00:42:15.220 align:middle line:84%
couple, not just some,
but every couple,

00:42:15.220 --> 00:42:19.390 align:middle line:84%
has a minimum of nine
irreconcilable differences.

00:42:19.390 --> 00:42:21.750 align:middle line:84%
These are things on
which you are never

00:42:21.750 --> 00:42:23.990 align:middle line:90%
ever going to agree on.

00:42:23.990 --> 00:42:27.160 align:middle line:84%
So knowing that, then
how do you co-exist?

00:42:27.160 --> 00:42:30.850 align:middle line:84%
With respect, and love, and
appreciation for each other,

00:42:30.850 --> 00:42:33.320 align:middle line:84%
and learning how to
communicate well,

00:42:33.320 --> 00:42:38.070 align:middle line:84%
and learning how to create what
he calls creative solutions.

00:42:38.070 --> 00:42:41.579 align:middle line:84%
So one example of that, also
came from Harville Hendrix,

00:42:41.579 --> 00:42:43.620 align:middle line:84%
because we were having
this conversation one day.

00:42:43.620 --> 00:42:46.280 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well,
creative solutions,

00:42:46.280 --> 00:42:47.600 align:middle line:90%
that sounds like a good idea.

00:42:47.600 --> 00:42:49.420 align:middle line:90%
Give me a concrete example.

00:42:49.420 --> 00:42:50.650 align:middle line:90%
He said I've got one for you.

00:42:50.650 --> 00:42:53.680 align:middle line:84%
He said my idea
of the perfect day

00:42:53.680 --> 00:42:56.400 align:middle line:84%
is to get behind the
wheel of a vehicle

00:42:56.400 --> 00:42:59.410 align:middle line:84%
and then drive for
eight or nine hours.

00:42:59.410 --> 00:43:03.310 align:middle line:84%
Helen, his wife and partner,
her idea of a perfect day

00:43:03.310 --> 00:43:07.410 align:middle line:84%
is to stay home and do
needle point or knitting.

00:43:07.410 --> 00:43:10.240 align:middle line:84%
Now, these are two
very different things.

00:43:10.240 --> 00:43:12.090 align:middle line:84%
I said, well, how did
you solve that one.

00:43:12.090 --> 00:43:15.550 align:middle line:84%
And he started to laugh and
he said we bought an RV.

00:43:15.550 --> 00:43:18.750 align:middle line:84%
I'm always driving and
she's always home, knitting.

00:43:18.750 --> 00:43:19.950 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:43:19.950 --> 00:43:21.934 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: So it
requires some effort.

00:43:21.934 --> 00:43:23.600 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: That's
creative, that's good.

00:43:23.600 --> 00:43:25.058 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: And it's
not a compromise.

00:43:25.058 --> 00:43:25.705 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: No.

00:43:25.705 --> 00:43:27.080 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: I don't
like compromise,

00:43:27.080 --> 00:43:30.020 align:middle line:84%
because you both
lose in a compromise.

00:43:30.020 --> 00:43:32.620 align:middle line:84%
But there are ways
for everybody to win.

00:43:32.620 --> 00:43:34.920 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes, it's
simple as learning

00:43:34.920 --> 00:43:36.700 align:middle line:90%
to grow a generous heart.

00:43:36.700 --> 00:43:40.240 align:middle line:84%
So I've always-- I hate
to use the word hated,

00:43:40.240 --> 00:43:42.000 align:middle line:90%
but hated sports on TV.

00:43:42.000 --> 00:43:44.160 align:middle line:84%
That was like a thing I
never ever wanted to do.

00:43:44.160 --> 00:43:47.150 align:middle line:84%
In fact, it was part of my
whole deal breaker thing.

00:43:47.150 --> 00:43:52.240 align:middle line:84%
I was not going to marry a guy
who watched football on TV.

00:43:52.240 --> 00:43:55.120 align:middle line:84%
So I marry a former
basketball player.

00:43:55.120 --> 00:43:56.620 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know about basketball.

00:43:56.620 --> 00:43:58.000 align:middle line:90%
Now, he loves basketball.

00:43:58.000 --> 00:44:00.010 align:middle line:84%
His whole family
loves basketball.

00:44:00.010 --> 00:44:02.497 align:middle line:84%
I never even knew
what basketball was.

00:44:02.497 --> 00:44:04.080 align:middle line:84%
But I thought, you
know, this has been

00:44:04.080 --> 00:44:06.330 align:middle line:90%
a big part of his entire life.

00:44:06.330 --> 00:44:09.340 align:middle line:84%
Maybe I could just watch
the last quarter of a game

00:44:09.340 --> 00:44:11.695 align:middle line:84%
with him when it's
important to him.

00:44:11.695 --> 00:44:13.682 align:middle line:90%
And so I started to do that.

00:44:13.682 --> 00:44:15.890 align:middle line:84%
And I still didn't like it
and I still didn't get it.

00:44:15.890 --> 00:44:19.030 align:middle line:84%
Until, one day, I'm watching
the last quarter of a game,

00:44:19.030 --> 00:44:22.330 align:middle line:84%
and I notice that
this really short guy

00:44:22.330 --> 00:44:24.330 align:middle line:90%
is making all the points.

00:44:24.330 --> 00:44:26.940 align:middle line:84%
And I said to Brian
who's that short guy.

00:44:26.940 --> 00:44:28.550 align:middle line:84%
He said, oh, that's
Avery Johnson.

00:44:28.550 --> 00:44:30.890 align:middle line:84%
He's one of the best
players in the NBA.

00:44:30.890 --> 00:44:32.612 align:middle line:84%
And then the light
bulb went off and I

00:44:32.612 --> 00:44:35.260 align:middle line:84%
thought I'm going to always
cheer for the shortest

00:44:35.260 --> 00:44:37.020 align:middle line:90%
guy on any team.

00:44:37.020 --> 00:44:38.810 align:middle line:84%
And that's how I got
skin in the game.

00:44:38.810 --> 00:44:41.000 align:middle line:84%
And that's how I learned
to love basketball.

00:44:41.000 --> 00:44:43.240 align:middle line:90%
Because it was important to him.

00:44:43.240 --> 00:44:45.340 align:middle line:84%
Now, for Brian,
he's a movie buff.

00:44:45.340 --> 00:44:46.750 align:middle line:90%
He loves movies.

00:44:46.750 --> 00:44:50.340 align:middle line:84%
And he likes really serious,
intellectual movies.

00:44:50.340 --> 00:44:53.700 align:middle line:84%
My favorite movie of all
time is "Legally Blonde."

00:44:53.700 --> 00:44:56.180 align:middle line:90%
I like a stupid, funny movies.

00:44:56.180 --> 00:44:59.200 align:middle line:84%
So he grew a generous
heart by always taking me

00:44:59.200 --> 00:45:02.390 align:middle line:84%
to any movie I want to go
to, even though he'd never

00:45:02.390 --> 00:45:05.840 align:middle line:84%
go alone to see "Beverly Hills
Chihuahua," another favorite

00:45:05.840 --> 00:45:07.900 align:middle line:90%
of mine.

00:45:07.900 --> 00:45:09.140 align:middle line:90%
But that's what you do.

00:45:09.140 --> 00:45:11.850 align:middle line:84%
You learn to love what
your beloved loves.

00:45:11.850 --> 00:45:13.030 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

