Let's talk about some of
the-- some of the-- this

00:45:16.510 --> 00:45:19.860 align:middle line:84%
is Dr. Gottman, again,
kind of deal killers,

00:45:19.860 --> 00:45:23.810 align:middle line:84%
and that is criticism,
contempt, defensiveness,

00:45:23.810 --> 00:45:25.500 align:middle line:90%
and stonewalling.

00:45:25.500 --> 00:45:27.380 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Yes, he calls
them the four horsemen

00:45:27.380 --> 00:45:28.205 align:middle line:90%
of the apocalypse.

00:45:28.205 --> 00:45:28.830 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:45:28.830 --> 00:45:31.250 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: So when he's
observing a couple,

00:45:31.250 --> 00:45:34.690 align:middle line:84%
one of the things he looks
for, if either party is rolling

00:45:34.690 --> 00:45:38.150 align:middle line:84%
their eyes, that is
a sign of contempt.

00:45:38.150 --> 00:45:38.900 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:45:38.900 --> 00:45:40.410 align:middle line:90%
That's very disrespectful.

00:45:40.410 --> 00:45:42.570 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: And that the
marriage isn't going to work.

00:45:42.570 --> 00:45:44.350 align:middle line:84%
So if somebody--
if your partner's

00:45:44.350 --> 00:45:46.890 align:middle line:84%
being super defensive or
they're stonewalling you

00:45:46.890 --> 00:45:49.540 align:middle line:84%
and they're refusing
to engage, that's

00:45:49.540 --> 00:45:51.450 align:middle line:84%
when you know you
need to go to therapy.

00:45:51.450 --> 00:45:53.590 align:middle line:84%
Reading a book is not
going to fix this.

00:45:53.590 --> 00:45:55.610 align:middle line:84%
You need to be with
a professional who

00:45:55.610 --> 00:45:57.580 align:middle line:90%
can guide you through it.

00:45:57.580 --> 00:45:59.500 align:middle line:84%
You know, on the
other piece of it,

00:45:59.500 --> 00:46:02.970 align:middle line:84%
one of-- another piece of
Gottman's amazing research

00:46:02.970 --> 00:46:04.960 align:middle line:84%
is that he noticed the
couples that do really

00:46:04.960 --> 00:46:09.480 align:middle line:84%
well always practice
what he calls bidding.

00:46:09.480 --> 00:46:12.270 align:middle line:84%
So when you turn your
body towards your partner

00:46:12.270 --> 00:46:15.930 align:middle line:84%
and you look them in the
eyes, you are bidding them.

00:46:15.930 --> 00:46:19.320 align:middle line:84%
You are putting your presence
and attention on them.

00:46:19.320 --> 00:46:21.660 align:middle line:84%
And they know it and
they can feel it.

00:46:21.660 --> 00:46:23.990 align:middle line:84%
And another thing I
just learned yesterday

00:46:23.990 --> 00:46:26.050 align:middle line:84%
is that as you're
doing this, if you're

00:46:26.050 --> 00:46:29.030 align:middle line:84%
looking into their
left eye, then you're

00:46:29.030 --> 00:46:31.860 align:middle line:90%
connecting on the heart level.

00:46:31.860 --> 00:46:35.320 align:middle line:84%
So anytime you want to have
a really deep conversation

00:46:35.320 --> 00:46:38.450 align:middle line:84%
with anybody, gaze
into their left eye.

00:46:38.450 --> 00:46:40.110 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: OK,
thank you for that.

00:46:40.110 --> 00:46:43.780 align:middle line:84%
And I have read that before,
very interesting and useful.

00:46:43.780 --> 00:46:46.760 align:middle line:84%
Also, another thing
along that line, and then

00:46:46.760 --> 00:46:50.030 align:middle line:84%
I went to get into the
rebuilding, and the oxytocin

00:46:50.030 --> 00:46:51.990 align:middle line:84%
development, and all
that, after the love

00:46:51.990 --> 00:46:54.910 align:middle line:84%
seems to have gone,
Harville Hendrix,

00:46:54.910 --> 00:47:00.950 align:middle line:84%
he termed criticism as an
actual act of violence.

00:47:00.950 --> 00:47:01.590 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yes.

00:47:01.590 --> 00:47:03.131 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And let's
talk about that.

00:47:03.131 --> 00:47:05.840 align:middle line:84%
Because people think
it's natural to be bitchy

00:47:05.840 --> 00:47:08.110 align:middle line:84%
or hurl a little something
at someone, which

00:47:08.110 --> 00:47:10.410 align:middle line:90%
I find personally devastating.

00:47:10.410 --> 00:47:11.280 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yeah.

00:47:11.280 --> 00:47:14.180 align:middle line:84%
Harville says that
there's no such thing

00:47:14.180 --> 00:47:18.590 align:middle line:84%
as constructive criticism,
that all criticism is

00:47:18.590 --> 00:47:20.340 align:middle line:90%
a form of violence.

00:47:20.340 --> 00:47:24.450 align:middle line:84%
And he requires his
students to take a vow

00:47:24.450 --> 00:47:28.280 align:middle line:84%
to be not critical with each
other, to be not judgmental.

00:47:28.280 --> 00:47:31.990 align:middle line:84%
Now, of course, we have to have
serious difficult conversations

00:47:31.990 --> 00:47:33.050 align:middle line:90%
at some point.

00:47:33.050 --> 00:47:36.400 align:middle line:84%
And so there's lots of little
tips on how to do this.

00:47:36.400 --> 00:47:40.720 align:middle line:84%
The first one is you want to get
yourself to a place of neutral.

00:47:40.720 --> 00:47:45.590 align:middle line:84%
You don't want to go in
bashing somebody's brains out.

00:47:45.590 --> 00:47:48.410 align:middle line:84%
So get yourself to neutral,
however you need to do that.

00:47:48.410 --> 00:47:53.036 align:middle line:84%
And then ask your partner,
you know, I have a problem.

00:47:53.036 --> 00:47:54.910 align:middle line:84%
There's something that's
really bothering me.

00:47:54.910 --> 00:47:56.430 align:middle line:90%
I need your help with it.

00:47:56.430 --> 00:47:59.680 align:middle line:84%
When could I have 10
minutes of your time?

00:47:59.680 --> 00:48:01.840 align:middle line:84%
So you're not saying
we need to talk.

00:48:01.840 --> 00:48:04.090 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Because that's--
everyone's frightened when

00:48:04.090 --> 00:48:04.785 align:middle line:90%
those words come out.

00:48:04.785 --> 00:48:06.840 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: That's like the doctor
saying to you you have cancer.

00:48:06.840 --> 00:48:07.260 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Exactly.

00:48:07.260 --> 00:48:09.480 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: So you never go
in there, we have to talk.

00:48:09.480 --> 00:48:12.220 align:middle line:84%
That is not going to-- you're
not going to win there.

00:48:12.220 --> 00:48:15.260 align:middle line:84%
So you just gently, kindly
say I have a problem.

00:48:15.260 --> 00:48:16.470 align:middle line:90%
I need your help with it.

00:48:16.470 --> 00:48:18.406 align:middle line:90%
When can I have 10 minutes?

00:48:18.406 --> 00:48:19.780 align:middle line:84%
Then when you get
the 10 minutes,

00:48:19.780 --> 00:48:23.320 align:middle line:84%
you need to know the first
three minutes are critical.

00:48:23.320 --> 00:48:26.840 align:middle line:84%
That will set the tone
for the rest of the time.

00:48:26.840 --> 00:48:31.570 align:middle line:84%
So you want to start by
saying I just really want

00:48:31.570 --> 00:48:34.160 align:middle line:84%
to acknowledge how hard
you've been working

00:48:34.160 --> 00:48:35.800 align:middle line:90%
to take care of the family.

00:48:35.800 --> 00:48:38.120 align:middle line:84%
And I was just over
the moon yesterday

00:48:38.120 --> 00:48:40.640 align:middle line:84%
when you were helping little
Johnny with this homework.

00:48:40.640 --> 00:48:43.110 align:middle line:84%
And thanks so much for
taking my mom to the doctor.

00:48:43.110 --> 00:48:44.910 align:middle line:84%
You have no idea how
much that means to me

00:48:44.910 --> 00:48:46.840 align:middle line:84%
and I probably don't
tell you often enough

00:48:46.840 --> 00:48:48.910 align:middle line:90%
how much I love you.

00:48:48.910 --> 00:48:51.160 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: However, there
are a couple things that--

00:48:51.160 --> 00:48:53.970 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: And here's what
happened last night when we

00:48:53.970 --> 00:48:56.180 align:middle line:84%
were at the party
with Bob and Joan.

00:48:56.180 --> 00:49:00.720 align:middle line:84%
And I know you would never, ever
deliberately hurt my feelings

00:49:00.720 --> 00:49:02.160 align:middle line:90%
or humiliate me.

00:49:02.160 --> 00:49:07.180 align:middle line:84%
But when you said X, Y, and
Z, I really felt A, B, and C.

00:49:07.180 --> 00:49:10.390 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sure it
wasn't on purpose.

00:49:10.390 --> 00:49:15.340 align:middle line:84%
Now, that's an opening for
an apology or a response,

00:49:15.340 --> 00:49:16.585 align:middle line:90%
as opposed to you stupid--

00:49:16.585 --> 00:49:18.140 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: It's
not an indictment.

00:49:18.140 --> 00:49:19.570 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Right.

00:49:19.570 --> 00:49:22.320 align:middle line:84%
And that's how we need
to talk with each other.

00:49:22.320 --> 00:49:25.800 align:middle line:84%
Because nobody wakes up
in the morning thinking,

00:49:25.800 --> 00:49:28.402 align:middle line:84%
wow, how could I
ruin Regina's day.

00:49:28.402 --> 00:49:29.110 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:49:29.110 --> 00:49:32.180 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: What could I do
today to really piss her off.

00:49:32.180 --> 00:49:35.802 align:middle line:84%
And yet we live like people
are hurting us on purpose.

00:49:35.802 --> 00:49:36.760 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: That's true.

00:49:36.760 --> 00:49:38.430 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: And they're not.

00:49:38.430 --> 00:49:39.430 align:middle line:90%
They're just like us.

00:49:39.430 --> 00:49:41.740 align:middle line:84%
They want to be loved
for who they are.

00:49:41.740 --> 00:49:43.430 align:middle line:90%
They want to be accepted.

00:49:43.430 --> 00:49:45.490 align:middle line:90%
They want to be acknowledged.

00:49:45.490 --> 00:49:48.080 align:middle line:84%
And yet we are like these
heat seeking missiles--

00:49:48.080 --> 00:49:49.965 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: We create
enemy camps almost.

00:49:49.965 --> 00:49:50.590 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Right.

00:49:50.590 --> 00:49:53.990 align:middle line:90%
You did this is me.

00:49:53.990 --> 00:49:56.660 align:middle line:84%
And maybe they did, but
they didn't mean to do it,

00:49:56.660 --> 00:49:58.220 align:middle line:90%
unless they're a psychopath.

00:49:58.220 --> 00:50:00.030 align:middle line:84%
In which case, you
know, call a lawyer.

00:50:00.030 --> 00:50:01.363 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: We need to get going.

00:50:01.363 --> 00:50:02.030 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, exactly.

00:50:02.030 --> 00:50:04.930 align:middle line:84%
And another thing is,
in partnership, people

00:50:04.930 --> 00:50:08.090 align:middle line:84%
tend to give what it is--
and I've seen this a lot--

00:50:08.090 --> 00:50:10.910 align:middle line:84%
they tend to give what it
is they want or needed,

00:50:10.910 --> 00:50:14.840 align:middle line:84%
instead of giving what the
other person wants or needs.

00:50:14.840 --> 00:50:17.450 align:middle line:84%
And it takes time
to decipher this

00:50:17.450 --> 00:50:19.030 align:middle line:90%
and have that conversation.

00:50:19.030 --> 00:50:22.390 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Yeah, and it can
be an easy conversation.

00:50:22.390 --> 00:50:24.240 align:middle line:84%
Let's say your
birthday is coming up.

00:50:24.240 --> 00:50:27.180 align:middle line:84%
It's like I know you haven't
forgotten that my birthday is

00:50:27.180 --> 00:50:30.840 align:middle line:84%
coming up and you probably
have ideas of what you want

00:50:30.840 --> 00:50:34.410 align:middle line:84%
to get me, but just in case
you don't have any ideas,

00:50:34.410 --> 00:50:38.590 align:middle line:84%
I actually was at the mall the
other day at X, Y, Z store.

00:50:38.590 --> 00:50:41.930 align:middle line:84%
And there's this white
dress in a size 10

00:50:41.930 --> 00:50:44.340 align:middle line:84%
called the Tahari
something something.

00:50:44.340 --> 00:50:48.050 align:middle line:84%
So just in case, you could
drop-- you can plants seeds.

00:50:48.050 --> 00:50:51.090 align:middle line:84%
But you do it with a sense of
humor and light-heartedness.

00:50:51.090 --> 00:50:53.970 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: But when
it goes the other way,

00:50:53.970 --> 00:50:57.220 align:middle line:84%
such as I remember one
situation, for a birthday,

00:50:57.220 --> 00:51:01.360 align:middle line:84%
where my partner was really big
into playing rugby and gave me

00:51:01.360 --> 00:51:03.930 align:middle line:84%
a rugby t-shirt
from a tournament,

00:51:03.930 --> 00:51:05.490 align:middle line:90%
as a birthday present.

00:51:05.490 --> 00:51:07.990 align:middle line:84%
And I thought I
don't wear t-shirts.

00:51:07.990 --> 00:51:09.200 align:middle line:90%
I'm not into rugby.

00:51:09.200 --> 00:51:11.990 align:middle line:84%
I thanked him for it,
but I thought we're not

00:51:11.990 --> 00:51:13.950 align:middle line:90%
on the same page here at all.

00:51:13.950 --> 00:51:15.840 align:middle line:84%
I mean why would he
think that I would

00:51:15.840 --> 00:51:18.070 align:middle line:90%
want to wear a rugby t-shirt.

00:51:18.070 --> 00:51:21.490 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Well, maybe because his
fantasy that he didn't express

00:51:21.490 --> 00:51:23.610 align:middle line:84%
was that you'd wear
it with nothing else.

00:51:23.610 --> 00:51:27.890 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Maybe there wasn't
any other requests along with

00:51:27.890 --> 00:51:29.120 align:middle line:90%
it, so to speak.

00:51:29.120 --> 00:51:31.760 align:middle line:84%
But, nonetheless, I
thought, huh, that's odd.

00:51:31.760 --> 00:51:32.110 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: And you could also--

00:51:32.110 --> 00:51:33.240 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I thanked
him, but I thought--

00:51:33.240 --> 00:51:35.739 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Put the t-shirt on
with some high heels and nothing

00:51:35.739 --> 00:51:38.930 align:middle line:84%
else and say you know what this
rugby t-shirt would look really

00:51:38.930 --> 00:51:40.740 align:middle line:90%
good with?

00:51:40.740 --> 00:51:42.742 align:middle line:84%
A diamond tennis
bracelet from Tiffany's.

00:51:42.742 --> 00:51:43.950 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: See, there you go.

00:51:43.950 --> 00:51:45.720 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't present
enough to do that.

00:51:45.720 --> 00:51:48.140 align:middle line:84%
I just said, oh, well,
thank you, Eddie.

00:51:48.140 --> 00:51:48.641 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:51:48.641 --> 00:51:50.556 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Yeah, he just
didn't know any better.

00:51:50.556 --> 00:51:52.160 align:middle line:84%
So if you had "The
Everything Book,"

00:51:52.160 --> 00:51:53.360 align:middle line:90%
he would have known better.

00:51:53.360 --> 00:51:53.740 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: That's
what I'm saying.

00:51:53.740 --> 00:51:56.220 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: He would have known
what sizes to get and where

00:51:56.220 --> 00:51:57.360 align:middle line:90%
to shop.

00:51:57.360 --> 00:52:00.340 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yeah, or just the
kindnesses that you appreciate

00:52:00.340 --> 00:52:01.640 align:middle line:90%
in life in general.

00:52:01.640 --> 00:52:03.300 align:middle line:84%
And the same thing,
I mean, we're

00:52:03.300 --> 00:52:06.860 align:middle line:84%
as lost on the other side
of knowing how to fulfill

00:52:06.860 --> 00:52:08.110 align:middle line:90%
someone else's desire.

00:52:08.110 --> 00:52:12.260 align:middle line:84%
So I love the idea
of the user's manual,

00:52:12.260 --> 00:52:15.510 align:middle line:84%
the-- what do you call it? "The
Everything Book," that's great.

00:52:15.510 --> 00:52:18.010 align:middle line:84%
OK, now, another
thing is listening.

00:52:18.010 --> 00:52:20.680 align:middle line:84%
As you say, this is so critical
because we may be listening,

00:52:20.680 --> 00:52:22.820 align:middle line:84%
but we're not actually
hearing what they're saying.

00:52:22.820 --> 00:52:26.590 align:middle line:84%
And so this listening technique
is listen, mirror, summarize,

00:52:26.590 --> 00:52:27.217 align:middle line:90%
validate.

00:52:27.217 --> 00:52:27.800 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yeah.

00:52:27.800 --> 00:52:28.550 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: So share that one.

00:52:28.550 --> 00:52:30.700 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: It's actually
called the Imago Dialogue,

00:52:30.700 --> 00:52:32.840 align:middle line:90%
which Harville Hendrix created.

00:52:32.840 --> 00:52:35.680 align:middle line:90%
So it's on page 255 in the book.

00:52:35.680 --> 00:52:37.740 align:middle line:84%
I actually give
you scripts on how

00:52:37.740 --> 00:52:39.032 align:middle line:90%
to have these conversations.

00:52:39.032 --> 00:52:39.840 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:52:39.840 --> 00:52:43.967 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: But so if you and I--
let's-- give me a complaint.

00:52:43.967 --> 00:52:46.550 align:middle line:84%
Pretend we're married and you're
going to give me a complaint.

00:52:46.550 --> 00:52:48.800 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: You leave the
toilet seat up all the time.

00:52:48.800 --> 00:52:53.140 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: OK, so what I heard you
say is that you're unhappy that

00:52:53.140 --> 00:52:54.970 align:middle line:84%
I always leave the
toilet seat up.

00:52:54.970 --> 00:52:55.990 align:middle line:90%
Is that right?

00:52:55.990 --> 00:52:56.660 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:52:56.660 --> 00:52:58.760 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Is there
any-- is there more?

00:52:58.760 --> 00:53:01.260 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: No, it's just that
I'm the one that has to end up

00:53:01.260 --> 00:53:03.125 align:middle line:90%
cleaning up the toilet seat.

00:53:03.125 --> 00:53:07.280 align:middle line:84%
And so it's icky and I don't--
I don't enjoy doing that.

00:53:07.280 --> 00:53:09.620 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: OK, so--
so I understand.

00:53:09.620 --> 00:53:12.890 align:middle line:84%
I leave the toilet seat up and
that just creates more work

00:53:12.890 --> 00:53:13.840 align:middle line:90%
for you, right?

00:53:13.840 --> 00:53:14.720 align:middle line:90%
Did I get that right?

00:53:14.720 --> 00:53:15.320 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: That's right.

00:53:15.320 --> 00:53:15.640 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: OK.

00:53:15.640 --> 00:53:17.030 align:middle line:84%
And is there
anything else that--

00:53:17.030 --> 00:53:19.280 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: That's pretty
much-- that's pretty much it.

00:53:19.280 --> 00:53:22.950 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: OK, so I understand and
I am going to make a commitment

00:53:22.950 --> 00:53:25.640 align:middle line:84%
to really try and do a
better job of not doing that.

00:53:25.640 --> 00:53:27.660 align:middle line:84%
Now, with the toilet
seat up, there's

00:53:27.660 --> 00:53:30.110 align:middle line:84%
even a better way to
go forward with that,

00:53:30.110 --> 00:53:34.456 align:middle line:84%
is just to say not only
was the toilet seat up,

00:53:34.456 --> 00:53:36.080 align:middle line:84%
but I got up in the
middle of the night

00:53:36.080 --> 00:53:37.450 align:middle line:90%
to go to the bathroom.

00:53:37.450 --> 00:53:39.930 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I just thought
I should have added that.

00:53:39.930 --> 00:53:44.450 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: And it was dark and my
butt landed in the cold water

00:53:44.450 --> 00:53:46.160 align:middle line:90%
and it was really gross.

00:53:46.160 --> 00:53:48.740 align:middle line:84%
And I know you didn't mean to
do it, but it was really awful.

00:53:48.740 --> 00:53:50.170 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: That is
the other part of it.

00:53:50.170 --> 00:53:51.950 align:middle line:84%
It occurred to me
after we wrapped it.

00:53:51.950 --> 00:53:53.450 align:middle line:90%
Yes, absolutely.

00:53:53.450 --> 00:53:56.180 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Yes, so the Imago
Dialogue's on page 255.

00:53:56.180 --> 00:54:00.280 align:middle line:84%
It's a really good thing to
have because communication's

00:54:00.280 --> 00:54:01.450 align:middle line:90%
different for everybody.

00:54:01.450 --> 00:54:05.725 align:middle line:84%
So we need-- I need to know that
I-- that I heard what you said

00:54:05.725 --> 00:54:07.952 align:middle line:84%
and that you knowledge
that I got it.

00:54:07.952 --> 00:54:08.660 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:54:08.660 --> 00:54:10.640 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: So we can
move to the next step.

00:54:10.640 --> 00:54:11.840 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:54:11.840 --> 00:54:16.390 align:middle line:84%
OK, now, you say part
of this whole journey

00:54:16.390 --> 00:54:19.340 align:middle line:84%
is once those
chemicals have worn off

00:54:19.340 --> 00:54:21.760 align:middle line:84%
and you're in the
reality soup of it all

00:54:21.760 --> 00:54:24.490 align:middle line:84%
and you're making your choice
and decisions day by day,

00:54:24.490 --> 00:54:27.970 align:middle line:84%
and you're really
attempting to listen,

00:54:27.970 --> 00:54:31.840 align:middle line:84%
to be as good a potential
mirror as you can

00:54:31.840 --> 00:54:35.530 align:middle line:84%
for the other person, and so
forth, the chemicals still

00:54:35.530 --> 00:54:36.530 align:middle line:90%
may be gone.

00:54:36.530 --> 00:54:40.110 align:middle line:84%
And then, a lot of times, other
aspects of the relationship,

00:54:40.110 --> 00:54:44.140 align:middle line:84%
the juicier parts, and maybe the
sexuality, starts dying back.

00:54:44.140 --> 00:54:47.510 align:middle line:84%
And in the book, you're
talking about the importance

00:54:47.510 --> 00:54:50.494 align:middle line:84%
of recreating
oxytocin production.

00:54:50.494 --> 00:54:51.410 align:middle line:90%
Let's talk about that.

00:54:51.410 --> 00:54:53.390 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: So the
first piece of this,

00:54:53.390 --> 00:54:56.090 align:middle line:84%
this is particularly
important for women,

00:54:56.090 --> 00:54:57.490 align:middle line:90%
is that we do too much.

00:54:57.490 --> 00:54:59.610 align:middle line:84%
So we're working, and
we're raising kids,

00:54:59.610 --> 00:55:01.430 align:middle line:84%
and we're taking care
of aging parents,

00:55:01.430 --> 00:55:04.009 align:middle line:84%
and there's financial stresses,
and we're giving, giving,

00:55:04.009 --> 00:55:06.180 align:middle line:84%
giving, and we're
stressed to the max.

00:55:06.180 --> 00:55:09.340 align:middle line:84%
And then we get bitchy because
we're stressed to the max

00:55:09.340 --> 00:55:11.590 align:middle line:84%
and we have nothing
else to give.

00:55:11.590 --> 00:55:14.180 align:middle line:84%
So the place that
we need to start

00:55:14.180 --> 00:55:17.220 align:middle line:84%
is to become what I
call a pleasure pig.

00:55:17.220 --> 00:55:19.340 align:middle line:84%
You need to put
yourself first and you

00:55:19.340 --> 00:55:22.430 align:middle line:84%
need to rebuild your
oxytocin levels.

00:55:22.430 --> 00:55:26.260 align:middle line:84%
Oxytocin is called the
super glue of love.

00:55:26.260 --> 00:55:29.110 align:middle line:84%
And there's fast, easy,
cheap ways to do this.

00:55:29.110 --> 00:55:34.720 align:middle line:84%
So the fastest way is to go get
a 20 second hug from somebody.

00:55:34.720 --> 00:55:36.470 align:middle line:90%
That rebuilds oxytocin.

00:55:36.470 --> 00:55:38.240 align:middle line:84%
You can get a
manicure, a pedicure.

00:55:38.240 --> 00:55:41.070 align:middle line:84%
Get your hair done, get a
massage, get a foot rub.

00:55:41.070 --> 00:55:43.180 align:middle line:84%
Go have drinks with
your girlfriends.

00:55:43.180 --> 00:55:45.160 align:middle line:90%
Tell somebody you love them.

00:55:45.160 --> 00:55:47.070 align:middle line:90%
Pet your dog, pet your cat.

00:55:47.070 --> 00:55:49.640 align:middle line:84%
All of these things
rebuild oxytocin.

00:55:49.640 --> 00:55:52.029 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: But take
responsibility for it yourself.

00:55:52.029 --> 00:55:52.820 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Every day.

00:55:52.820 --> 00:55:53.528 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:55:53.528 --> 00:55:57.160 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: When you make your to
do list, put, number one item,

00:55:57.160 --> 00:55:58.970 align:middle line:90%
pleasure today.

00:55:58.970 --> 00:56:01.160 align:middle line:84%
So, sometimes,
like twice a week,

00:56:01.160 --> 00:56:03.680 align:middle line:90%
I go get a 30 minute foot rub.

00:56:03.680 --> 00:56:06.200 align:middle line:84%
And I have this woman who
charges me a dollar a minute.

00:56:06.200 --> 00:56:07.160 align:middle line:90%
It's perfect.

00:56:07.160 --> 00:56:09.990 align:middle line:84%
On days when I'm too busy or I
don't want to spend any money,

00:56:09.990 --> 00:56:13.010 align:middle line:84%
I go to my playlist
and I listen to Andrea

00:56:13.010 --> 00:56:16.180 align:middle line:84%
Bocelli sing "The Prayer"
for four and a half minutes.

00:56:16.180 --> 00:56:18.550 align:middle line:90%
Fills me up with oxytocin.

00:56:18.550 --> 00:56:21.990 align:middle line:84%
Now, for men, who also get
stressed out, what they need

00:56:21.990 --> 00:56:24.590 align:middle line:90%
to do is rebuild testosterone.

00:56:24.590 --> 00:56:26.715 align:middle line:84%
So they can do that by
hanging out with the guys--

00:56:26.715 --> 00:56:28.090 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Watching
a game on TV.

00:56:28.090 --> 00:56:29.070 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Watching sports.

00:56:29.070 --> 00:56:30.111 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah, exactly.

00:56:30.111 --> 00:56:32.260 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: It's the
fastest way for most men.

00:56:32.260 --> 00:56:36.180 align:middle line:84%
Chopping wood, playing
sports, all of those things

00:56:36.180 --> 00:56:37.820 align:middle line:90%
rebuild testosterone.

00:56:37.820 --> 00:56:41.030 align:middle line:84%
So in order for
us to keep giving,

00:56:41.030 --> 00:56:43.530 align:middle line:84%
we have to fill
ourselves back up.

00:56:43.530 --> 00:56:48.340 align:middle line:84%
So if you're committed to
rebuilding your relationship,

00:56:48.340 --> 00:56:51.610 align:middle line:84%
first you have to fill up
your own love reservoir.

00:56:51.610 --> 00:56:52.860 align:middle line:90%
And that's self-love.

00:56:52.860 --> 00:56:55.760 align:middle line:84%
And so many people
see this as selfish,

00:56:55.760 --> 00:56:59.800 align:middle line:90%
but the truth is it's selfless.

00:56:59.800 --> 00:57:04.380 align:middle line:84%
You will have more to give when
you fill yourself up first.

00:57:04.380 --> 00:57:05.380 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Absolutely.

00:57:05.380 --> 00:57:09.260 align:middle line:84%
So-- and then, finally,
one other thing, because we

00:57:09.260 --> 00:57:10.450 align:middle line:90%
are about out of time.

00:57:10.450 --> 00:57:13.050 align:middle line:90%
And that is vulnerability.

00:57:13.050 --> 00:57:16.050 align:middle line:84%
This whole thing of
vulnerability and fear,

00:57:16.050 --> 00:57:18.360 align:middle line:84%
we're afraid of
being vulnerable.

00:57:18.360 --> 00:57:20.950 align:middle line:84%
And just give us a
quick peek at what

00:57:20.950 --> 00:57:24.197 align:middle line:84%
that means to allow ourselves to
be vulnerable with one another.

00:57:24.197 --> 00:57:24.780 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yeah.

00:57:24.780 --> 00:57:26.360 align:middle line:90%
So you and I are together.

00:57:26.360 --> 00:57:27.660 align:middle line:90%
We've just had this fight.

00:57:27.660 --> 00:57:31.140 align:middle line:84%
You've said some really
un-nice things to me.

00:57:31.140 --> 00:57:34.930 align:middle line:84%
And I could scream and yell
back or I could say, wow,

00:57:34.930 --> 00:57:38.530 align:middle line:90%
I'm feeling so hurt right now.

00:57:38.530 --> 00:57:43.680 align:middle line:84%
I can't believe that I am
on the verge of hysteria.

00:57:43.680 --> 00:57:46.680 align:middle line:10%
And I know you didn't mean
to hurt me this deeply,

00:57:46.680 --> 00:57:50.930 align:middle line:10%
but I need to take a few minutes
and pull myself together.

00:57:50.930 --> 00:57:53.992 align:middle line:10%
And let's talk in a half hour.

00:57:53.992 --> 00:57:55.700 align:middle line:10%
That's being really
vulnerable and that's

00:57:55.700 --> 00:57:58.570 align:middle line:10%
taking responsibility
for your own feelings.

00:57:58.570 --> 00:58:00.240 align:middle line:10%
And it's hard to do.

00:58:00.240 --> 00:58:02.052 align:middle line:10%
It's much easier to lash out.

00:58:02.052 --> 00:58:02.760 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:58:02.760 --> 00:58:05.260 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: But you have to say
what's true for you from an "I"

00:58:05.260 --> 00:58:08.411 align:middle line:84%
place and how it is for you,
as opposed to accusing them.

00:58:08.411 --> 00:58:09.910 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And let
yourself be seen.

00:58:09.910 --> 00:58:11.190 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Yes.

00:58:11.190 --> 00:58:12.110 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:58:12.110 --> 00:58:14.740 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And we're so often
trying to position ourselves

00:58:14.740 --> 00:58:17.490 align:middle line:84%
and hide who we are from one
another in life in general

00:58:17.490 --> 00:58:20.570 align:middle line:84%
by putting the
best face forward.

00:58:20.570 --> 00:58:21.070 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:58:21.070 --> 00:58:23.403 align:middle line:84%
So there's no room for that
in an intimate relationship.

00:58:23.403 --> 00:58:24.200 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: No.

00:58:24.200 --> 00:58:25.180 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Final words?

00:58:25.180 --> 00:58:25.740 align:middle line:90%
Quickly.

00:58:25.740 --> 00:58:28.890 align:middle line:84%
>> FORD: Yeah, the thing I would
say that I know for sure is

00:58:28.890 --> 00:58:31.990 align:middle line:84%
that if you're with somebody
that you once believed was

00:58:31.990 --> 00:58:36.570 align:middle line:84%
your soulmate, I would encourage
you to give it six months

00:58:36.570 --> 00:58:40.300 align:middle line:84%
of taking baby steps and just
doing a few things that are

00:58:40.300 --> 00:58:42.180 align:middle line:84%
in ""Turn Your Mate
Into Your Soulmate"

00:58:42.180 --> 00:58:45.360 align:middle line:84%
to see if you can reignite
and reenvision the one that

00:58:45.360 --> 00:58:46.305 align:middle line:90%
you're with.

00:58:46.305 --> 00:58:47.180 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Very good.

00:58:47.180 --> 00:58:50.840 align:middle line:84%
Well, very useful information,
very-- a fun journey with you.

00:58:50.840 --> 00:58:51.780 align:middle line:90%
Thank you so much.

00:58:51.780 --> 00:58:52.715 align:middle line:90%
>> FORD: Thank you.

